ame of the one was Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided. His brother's name was Joktan.UAJoktan became the father of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,UHadoram, Uzal, Diklah,UObal, Abimael, Sheba,U=Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan.UQTheir dwelling was from Mesha, as you go toward Sephar, the mountain of the east.UmThese are the sons of Shem, after their families, after their languages, in their lands, after their nations.UñThese are the families of the sons of Noah, after their generations, in their nations. Of these were the nations divided in the earth after the flood.t(NU6The whole earth was of one language and of one speech.UhIt happened, as they traveled east, that they found a plain in the land of Shinar, and they lived there.UÜThey said one to another, "Come, let's make bricks, and burn them thoroughly." They had brick for stone, and they used tar for mortar.U∫They said, "Come, let's build ourselves a city, and a tower whose top reaches to the sky, and let's make ourselves a name, lest we be scattered abroad on the surface of the whole earth."UPYahweh came down to see the city and the tower, which the children of men built.UÆYahweh said, "Behold, they are one people, and they have all one language, and this is what they begin to do. Now nothing will be withheld from them, which they intend to do.UjCome, let's go down, and there confuse their language, that they may not understand one another's speech."UkSo Yahweh scattered them abroad from there on the surface of all the earth. They stopped building the city.U´Therefore its name was called Babel, because there Yahweh confused the language of all the earth. From there, Yahweh scattered them abroad on the surface of all the earth.UçThis is the history of the generations of Shem. Shem was one hundred years old and became the father of Arpachshad two years after the flood.UtShem lived five hundred years after he became the father of Arpachshad, and became the father of sons and daughters.UCArpachshad lived thirty-five years and became the father of Shelah.U|Arpachshad lived four hundred three years after he became the father of Shelah, and became the father of sons and daughters.U9Shelah lived thirty years, and became the father of Eber:Uzand Shelah lived four hundred three years after he became the father of Eber, and became the father of sons and daughters.U=Eber lived thirty-four years, and became the father of Peleg.UvEber lived four hundred thirty years after he became the father of Peleg, and became the father of sons and daughters.U7Peleg lived thirty years, and became the father of Reu.UrPeleg lived two hundred nine years after he became the father of Reu, and became the father of sons and daughters.U;Reu lived thirty-two years, and became the father of Serug.UsReu lived two hundred seven years after he became the father of Serug, and became the father of sons and daughters.U9Serug lived thirty years, and became the father of Nahor.UoSerug lived two hundred years after he became the father of Nahor, and became the father of sons and daughters.U>Nahor lived twenty-nine years, and became the father of Terah.UxNahor lived one hundred nineteen years after he became the father of Terah, and became the father of sons and daughters.ULTerah lived seventy years, and became the father of Abram, Nahor, and Haran.UàNow this is the history of the generations of Terah. Terah became the father of Abram, Nahor, and Haran. Haran became the father of Lot.USHaran died before his father Terah in the land of his birth, in Ur of the Chaldees.UùAbram and Nahor took wives. The name of Abram's wife was Sarai, and the name of Nahor's wife, Milcah, the daughter of Haran who was also the father of Iscah.U#Sarai was barren. She had no child.UﬂTerah took Abram his son, Lot the son of Haran, his son's son, and Sarai his daughter-in-law, his son Abram's wife. They went forth from Ur of the Chaldees, to go into the land of Canaan. They came to Haran and lived there.UCThe days of Terah were two hundred five years. Terah died in Haran.t(NUåNow Yahweh said to Abram, "Get out of your country, and from your relatives, and from your father's house, to the land that I will show you.UeI will make of you a great nation. I will bless you and make your name great. You will be a blessing.UÄI will bless those who bless you, and I will curse him who curses you. In you will all of the families of the earth be blessed."U~So Abram went, as Yahweh had spoken to him. Lot went with him. Abram was seventy-five years old when he departed out of Haran.U‡Abram took Sarai his wife, Lot his brother's son, all their substance that they had gathered, and the souls whom they had gotten in Haran, and they went forth to go into the land of Canaan. Into the land of Canaan they came.UoAbram passed through the land to the place of Shechem, to the oak of Moreh. The Canaanite was then in the land.UÄYahweh appeared to Abram and said, "I will give this land to your seed." He built an altar there to Yahweh, who appeared to him.U¬He left from there to the mountain on the east of Bethel, and pitched his tent, having Bethel on the west, and Ai on the east. There he built an altar to Yahweh and called on the name of Yahweh.U0Abram traveled, going on still toward the South.UThere was a famine in the land. Abram went down into Egypt to live as a foreigner there, for the famine was severe in the land.UéIt happened, when he had come near to enter Egypt, that he said to Sarai his wife, "See now, I know that you are a beautiful woman to look at.UâIt will happen, when the Egyptians will see you, that they will say, 'This is his wife.' They will kill me, but they will save you alive.UxPlease say that you are my sister, that it may be well with me for your sake, and that my soul may live because of you."UeIt happened that when Abram had come into Egypt, the Egyptians saw that the woman was very beautiful.UiThe princes of Pharaoh saw her, and praised her to Pharaoh; and