nging water.UñThe herdsmen of Gerar argued with Isaac's herdsmen, saying, "The water is ours." He called the name of the well Esek, because they contended with him.URThey dug another well, and they argued over that, also. He called its name Sitnah.U∂He left that place, and dug another well. They didn't argue over that one. He called it Rehoboth. He said, "For now Yahweh has made room for us, and we will be fruitful in the land."U#He went up from there to Beersheba.U≈Yahweh appeared to him the same night, and said, "I am the God of Abraham your father. Don't be afraid, for I am with you, and will bless you, and multiply your seed for my servant Abraham's sake."UyHe built an altar there, and called on the name of Yahweh, and pitched his tent there. There Isaac's servants dug a well.UcThen Abimelech went to him from Gerar, and Ahuzzath his friend, and Phicol the captain of his army.UaIsaac said to them, "Why have you come to me, since you hate me, and have sent me away from you?"U°They said, "We saw plainly that Yahweh was with you. We said, 'Let there now be an oath between us, even between us and you, and let us make a covenant with you,U´that you will do us no harm, as we have not touched you, and as we have done to you nothing but good, and have sent you away in peace.' You are now the blessed of Yahweh."U-He made them a feast, and they ate and drank.U{They rose up some time in the morning, and swore one to another. Isaac sent them away, and they departed from him in peace.UíIt happened the same day, that Isaac's servants came, and told him concerning the well which they had dug, and said to him, "We have found water."UMHe called it Shibah. Therefore the name of the city is Beersheba to this day.UâWhen Esau was forty years old, he took as wife Judith, the daughter of Beeri the Hittite, and Basemath, the daughter of Elon the Hittite.U+They grieved Isaac's and Rebekah's spirits.t(NU¨It happened, that when Isaac was old, and his eyes were dim, so that he could not see