e this day throughout your generations by an ordinance forever.UñIn the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month at evening, you shall eat unleavened bread, until the twenty first day of the month at evening.UÿSeven days shall there be no yeast found in your houses, for whoever eats that which is leavened, that soul shall be cut off from the congregation of Israel, whether he be a foreigner, or one who is born in the land.UYYou shall eat nothing leavened. In all your habitations you shall eat unleavened bread.'"UéThen Moses called for all the elders of Israel, and said to them, "Draw out, and take lambs according to your families, and kill the Passover.UÈYou shall take a bunch of hyssop, and dip it in the blood that is in the basin, and strike the lintel and the two doorposts with the blood that is in the basin; and none of you shall go out of the door of his house until the morning.U„For Yahweh will pass through to strike the Egyptians; and when he sees the blood on the lintel, and on the two doorposts, Yahweh will pass over the door, and will not allow the destroyer to come in to your houses to strike you.UNYou shall observe this thing for an ordinance to you and to your sons forever.UäIt shall happen when you have come to the land which Yahweh will give you, according as he has promised, that you shall keep this service.UOIt will happen, when your children ask you, 'What do you mean by this service?'U‡that you shall say, 'It is the sacrifice of Yahweh's Passover, who passed over the houses of the children of Israel in Egypt, when he struck the Egyptians, and spared our houses.'" The people bowed their heads and worshiped.U]The children of Israel went and did so; as Yahweh had commanded Moses and Aaron, so they did.U„It happened at midnight, that Yahweh struck all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, from the firstborn of Pharaoh who sat on his throne to the firstborn of the captive who was in the dungeon; and all the firstborn of livestock.U™Pharaoh rose up