t Yahweh."UàMoses said to Aaron, "Tell all the congregation of the children of Israel, 'Come near before Yahweh, for he has heard your murmurings.'"UØIt happened, as Aaron spoke to the whole congregation of the children of Israel, that they looked toward the wilderness, and behold, the glory of Yahweh appeared in the cloud.UYahweh spoke to Moses, saying,U—"I have heard the murmurings of the children of Israel. Speak to them, saying, 'At evening you shall eat meat, and in the morning you shall be filled with bread: and you shall know that I am Yahweh your God.'"UoIt happened at evening that quail came up and covered the camp; and in the morning the dew lay around the camp.UÉWhen the dew that lay had gone, behold, on the surface of the wilderness was a small round thing, small as the frost on the ground.U∂When the children of Israel saw it, they said one to another, "What is it?" For they didn't know what it was. Moses said to them, "It is the bread which Yahweh has given you to eat."U”This is the thing which Yahweh has commanded: "Gather of it everyone according to his eating; an omer a head, according to the number of your persons, you shall take it, every man for those who are in his tent."UAThe children of Israel did so, and gathered some more, some less.U£When they measured it with an omer, he who gathered much had nothing over, and he who gathered little had no lack. They gathered every man according to his eating.U?Moses said to them, "Let no one leave of it until the morning."UûNotwithstanding they didn't listen to Moses, but some of them left of it until the morning, and it bred worms, and became foul: and Moses was angry with them.UhThey gathered it morning by morning, everyone according to his eating. When the sun grew hot, it melted.UòIt happened that on the sixth day they gathered twice as much bread, two omers for each one, and all the rulers of the congregation came and told Moses.T␀␀He said to them, "This is that which Yahweh has spoken, 'Tomorrow is a solemn rest, a holy Sabbath to Yahweh. Bake that which you want to bake, and boil that which you want to boil; and all that remains over lay up for yourselves to be kept until the morning.'"UoThey laid it up until the morning, as Moses asked, and it didn't become foul, neither was there any worm in it.UhMoses said, "Eat that today, for today is a Sabbath to Yahweh. Today you shall not find it in the field.U`Six days you shall gather it, but on the seventh day is the Sabbath. In it there shall be none."U`It happened on the seventh day, that some of the people went out to gather, and they found none.URYahweh said to Moses, "How long do you refuse to keep my commandments and my laws?U¿Behold, because Yahweh has given you the Sabbath, therefore he gives you on the sixth day the bread of two days. Everyone stay in his place. Let no one go out of his place on the seventh day."U(So the people rested on the seventh day.U{The house of Israel called its name Manna, and it was like coriander seed, white; and its taste was like wafers with honey.UÓMoses said, "This is the thing which Yahweh has commanded, 'Let an omer-full of it be kept throughout your generations, that they may see the bread with which I fed you in the wilderness, when I brought you forth from the land of Egypt.'"UåMoses said to Aaron, "Take a pot, and put an omer-full of manna in it, and lay it up before Yahweh, to be kept throughout your generations."UPAs Yahweh commanded Moses, so Aaron laid it up before the Testimony, to be kept.U†The children of Israel ate the manna forty years, until they came to an inhabited land. They ate the manna until they came to the borders of the land of Canaan.U*Now an omer is the tenth part of an ephah.t(NU”All the congregation of the children of Israel traveled from the wilderness of Sin, by their journeys, according to Yahweh's commandment, and encamped in Rephidim; but there was no water for the people to drink.UòTherefore the people quarreled with Moses, and said, "Give