, remains to the morning, then you shall burn the remainder with fire: it shall not be eaten, because it is holy.U}"You shall do so to Aaron, and to his sons, according to all that I have commanded you. You shall consecrate them seven days.U´Every day you shall offer the bull of sin offering for atonement: and you shall cleanse the altar, when you make atonement for it; and you shall anoint it, to sanctify it.UèSeven days you shall make atonement for the altar, and sanctify it: and the altar shall be most holy; whatever touches the altar shall be holy.Ub"Now this is that which you shall offer on the altar: two lambs a year old day by day continually.U[The one lamb you shall offer in the morning; and the other lamb you shall offer at evening:U™and with the one lamb a tenth part of an ephah of fine flour mixed with the fourth part of a hin of beaten oil, and the fourth part of a hin of wine for a drink offering.UÀThe other lamb you shall offer at evening, and shall do to it according to the meal offering of the morning, and according to its drink offering, for a pleasant aroma, an offering made by fire to Yahweh.UßIt shall be a continual burnt offering throughout your generations at the door of the Tent of Meeting before Yahweh, where I will meet with you, to speak there to you.U]There I will meet with the children of Israel; and the place shall be sanctified by my glory.UÖI will sanctify the Tent of Meeting and the altar: Aaron also and his sons I will sanctify, to minister to me in the priest's office.UAI will dwell among the children of Israel, and will be their God.UíThey shall know that I am Yahweh their God, who brought them forth out of the land of Egypt, that I might dwell among them: I am Yahweh their God.t(NUN"You shall make an altar to burn incense on. You shall make it of acacia wood.UñIts length shall be a cubit, and its breadth a cubit. It shall be square, and its height shall be two cubits. Its horns shall be of one piece with it.U~You shall overlay it 