't redeemed, then it shall be sold according to your valuation.Uﬁ"'Notwithstanding, no devoted thing, that a man shall devote to Yahweh of all that he has, whether of man or animal, or of the field of his possession, shall be sold or redeemed: every devoted thing is most holy to Yahweh.Uj"'No one devoted, who shall be devoted from among men, shall be ransomed; he shall surely be put to death.U}"'All the tithe of the land, whether of the seed of the land or of the fruit of the trees, is Yahweh's. It is holy to Yahweh.UHIf a man redeems anything of his tithe, he shall add a fifth part to it.UkAll the tithe of the herds or the flocks, whatever passes under the rod, the tenth shall be holy to Yahweh.U¿He shall not search whether it is good or bad, neither shall he change it: and if he changes it at all, then both it and that for which it is changed shall be holy. It shall not be redeemed.'"UbThese are the commandments which Yahweh commanded Moses for the children of Israel on Mount Sinai.ttq(UNumbers(NU∏Yahweh spoke to Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, in the Tent of Meeting, on the first day of the second month, in the second year after they had come out of the land of Egypt, saying,U¨"Take a census of all the congregation of the children of Israel, by their families, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of the names, every male, one by one;UÇfrom twenty years old and upward, all who are able to go out to war in Israel. You and Aaron shall number them by their divisions.URWith you there shall be a man of every tribe; everyone head of his fathers' house.U^These are the names of the men who shall stand with you: Of Reuben: Elizur the son of Shedeur.U,Of Simeon: Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.U'Of Judah: Nahshon the son of Amminadab.U&Of Issachar: Nethanel the son of Zuar.U#Of Zebulun: Eliab the son of Helon.UnOf the children of Joseph: Of Ephraim: Elishama the son of Ammihud. Of Manasseh: Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.U'Of Benjamin: Abidan the son of Gide