ahweh in its appointed season, that man shall bear his sin.T␀␀␀If a foreigner lives among you, and desires to keep the Passover to Yahweh; according to the statute of the Passover, and according to its ordinance, so shall he do. You shall have one statute, both for the foreigner, and for him who is born in the land.'"UÀOn the day that the tabernacle was raised up, the cloud covered the tabernacle, even the Tent of the Testimony: and at evening it was over the tabernacle as it were the appearance of fire, until morning.UQSo it was continually. The cloud covered it, and the appearance of fire by night.U∂Whenever the cloud was taken up from over the Tent, then after that the children of Israel traveled; and in the place where the cloud remained, there the children of Israel encamped.U∂At the commandment of Yahweh, the children of Israel traveled, and at the commandment of Yahweh they encamped. As long as the cloud remained on the tabernacle they remained encamped.UxWhen the cloud stayed on the tabernacle many days, then the children of Israel kept Yahweh's command, and didn't travel.U≥Sometimes the cloud was a few days on the tabernacle; then according to the commandment of Yahweh they remained encamped, and according to the commandment of Yahweh they traveled.U∂Sometimes the cloud was from evening until morning; and when the cloud was taken up in the morning, they traveled: or by day and by night, when the cloud was taken up, they traveled.UŒWhether it was two days, or a month, or a year that the cloud stayed on the tabernacle, remaining on it, the children of Israel remained encamped, and didn't travel; but when it was taken up, they traveled.UûAt the commandment of Yahweh they encamped, and at the commandment of Yahweh they traveled. They kept Yahweh's command, at the commandment of Yahweh by Moses.t(NUYahweh spoke to Moses, saying,Uû"Make two trumpets of silver. You shall make them of beaten work. You shall use them for the calling of the congregation, and for the journeying of the camps.UlWhen they blow them, all the congregation shall gather themselves to you at the door of the Tent of Meeting.UnIf they blow just one, then the princes, the heads of the thousands of Israel, shall gather themselves to you.UMWhen you blow an alarm, the camps that lie on the east side shall go forward.UãWhen you blow an alarm the second time, the camps that lie on the south side shall go forward. They shall blow an alarm for their journeys.UcBut when the assembly is to be gathered together, you shall blow, but you shall not sound an alarm.UÄThe sons of Aaron, the priests, shall blow the trumpets. This shall be to you for a statute forever throughout your generations.U÷When you go to war in your land against the adversary who oppresses you, then you shall sound an alarm with the trumpets. Then you will be remembered before Yahweh your God, and you will be saved from your enemies.T␀␀"Also in the day of your gladness, and in your set feasts, and in the beginnings of your months, you shall blow the trumpets over your burnt offerings, and over the sacrifices of your peace offerings; and they shall be to you for a memorial before your God. I am Yahweh your God."UûIt happened in the second year, in the second month, on the twentieth day of the month, that the cloud was taken up from over the tabernacle of the testimony.UèThe children of Israel went forward according to their journeys out of the wilderness of Sinai; and the cloud abode in the wilderness of Paran.UHThey first went forward according to the commandment of Yahweh by Moses.UêFirst, the standard of the camp of the children of Judah went forward according to their armies. Nahshon the son of Amminadab was over his army.UTNethanel the son of Zuar was over the army of the tribe of the children of Issachar.UQEliab the son of Helon was over the army of the tribe of the children of Zebulun.UuThe tabernacle was taken down; and the sons of Gershon and the sons of Merari, who bore the tabernacle, 