hon the Amorite, king of Heshbon, and his land; begin to possess it, and contend with him in battle.UƒThis day will I begin to put the dread of you and the fear of you on the peoples who are under the whole sky, who shall hear the report of you, and shall tremble, and be in anguish because of you.UiI sent messengers out of the wilderness of Kedemoth to Sihon king of Heshbon with words of peace, saying,UuLet me pass through your land: I will go along by the highway, I will turn neither to the right hand nor to the left.UÖYou shall sell me food for money, that I may eat; and give me water for money, that I may drink: only let me pass through on my feet,Ußas the children of Esau who dwell in Seir, and the Moabites who dwell in Ar, did to me; until I shall pass over the Jordan into the land which Yahweh our God gives us.U∏But Sihon king of Heshbon would not let us pass by him; for Yahweh your God hardened his spirit, and made his heart obstinate, that he might deliver him into your hand, as at this day.UÖYahweh said to me, Behold, I have begun to deliver up Sihon and his land before you: begin to possess, that you may inherit his land.UJThen Sihon came out against us, he and all his people, to battle at Jahaz.U_Yahweh our God delivered him up before us; and we struck him, and his sons, and all his people.UåWe took all his cities at that time, and utterly destroyed every inhabited city, with the women and the little ones; we left none remaining:Udonly the livestock we took for a prey to ourselves, with the spoil of the cities which we had taken.U»From Aroer, which is on the edge of the valley of the Arnon, and [from] the city that is in the valley, even to Gilead, there was not a city too high for us; Yahweh our God delivered up all before us:U≠only to the land of the children of Ammon you didn't come near; all the side of the river Jabbok, and the cities of the hill country, and wherever Yahweh our God forbade us.t(NUàThen we turned, and went up the way to Bashan: and Og the king of Bashan came out against us, he and all his people, to battle at Edrei.U∆Yahweh said to me, Don't fear him; for I have delivered him, and all his people, and his land, into your hand; and you shall do to him as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon.UíSo Yahweh our God delivered into our hand Og also, the king of Bashan, and all his people: and we struck him until none was left to him remaining.UùWe took all his cities at that time; there was not a city which we didn't take from them; sixty cities, all the region of Argob, the kingdom of Og in Bashan.UjAll these were cities fortified with high walls, gates, and bars; besides the unwalled towns a great many.UãWe utterly destroyed them, as we did to Sihon king of Heshbon, utterly destroying every inhabited city, with the women and the little ones.UTBut all the livestock, and the spoil of the cities, we took for a prey to ourselves.UòWe took the land at that time out of the hand of the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, from the valley of the Arnon to Mount Hermon;UK([which] Hermon the Sidonians call Sirion, and the Amorites call it Senir;)Uyall the cities of the plain, and all Gilead, and all Bashan, to Salecah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan.UÒ(For only Og king of Bashan remained of the remnant of the Rephaim; behold, his bedstead was a bedstead of iron; isn't it in Rabbah of the children of Ammon? nine cubits was its length, and four cubits its breadth, after the cubit of a man.)U¿This land we took in possession at that time: from Aroer, which is by the valley of the Arnon, and half the hill country of Gilead, and its cities, gave I to the Reubenites and to the Gadites:U≥and the rest of Gilead, and all Bashan, the kingdom of Og, gave I to the half-tribe of Manasseh; all the region of Argob, even all Bashan. (The same is called the land of Rephaim.UπJair the son of Manasseh took all the region of Argob, to the border of the Geshurites and the Maaca