ances, which you shall teach them, that they may do them in the land which I give them to possess it.UÇYou shall observe to do therefore as Yahweh your God has commanded you: you shall not turn aside to the right hand or to the left.U√You shall walk in all the way which Yahweh your God has commanded you, that you may live, and that it may be well with you, and that you may prolong your days in the land which you shall possess.t(NU∞Now this is the commandment, the statutes, and the ordinances, which Yahweh your God commanded to teach you, that you might do them in the land where you go over to possess it;Uœthat you might fear Yahweh your God, to keep all his statutes and his commandments, which I command you, you, and your son, and your son's son, all the days of your life; and that your days may be prolonged.UœHear therefore, Israel, and observe to do it; that it may be well with you, and that you may increase mightily, as Yahweh, the God of your fathers, has promised to you, in a land flowing with milk and honey.U/Hear, Israel: Yahweh is our God; Yahweh is one:Uhand you shall love Yahweh your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your might.UBThese words, which I command you this day, shall be on your heart;U≥and you shall teach them diligently to your children, and shall talk of them when you sit in your house, and when you walk by the way, and when you lie down, and when you rise up.U]You shall bind them for a sign on your hand, and they shall be for symbols between your eyes.UHYou shall write them on the door posts of your house, and on your gates.U¡It shall be, when Yahweh your God shall bring you into the land which he swore to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give you, great and goodly cities, which you didn't build,U∏and houses full of all good things, which you didn't fill, and cisterns dug out, which you didn't dig, vineyards and olive trees, which you didn't plant, and you shall eat and be full;Upthen beware les