 angel of Yahweh came up from Gilgal to Bochim. He said, I made you to go up out of Egypt, and have brought you to the land which I swore to your fathers; and I said, I will never break my covenant with you:U£and you shall make no covenant with the inhabitants of this land; you shall break down their altars. But you have not listened to my voice: why have you done this?UñTherefore I also said, I will not drive them out from before you; but they shall be [as thorns] in your sides, and their gods shall be a snare to you.UáIt happened, when the angel of Yahweh spoke these words to all the children of Israel, that the people lifted up their voice, and wept.UOThey called the name of that place Bochim: and they sacrificed there to Yahweh.UwNow when Joshua had sent the people away, the children of Israel went every man to his inheritance to possess the land.U≠The people served Yahweh all the days of Joshua, and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua, who had seen all the great work of Yahweh that he had worked for Israel.UTJoshua the son of Nun, the servant of Yahweh, died, being one hundred ten years old.UâThey buried him in the border of his inheritance in Timnath Heres, in the hill country of Ephraim, on the north of the mountain of Gaash.U∞Also all that generation were gathered to their fathers: and there arose another generation after them, who didn't know Yahweh, nor yet the work which he had worked for Israel.U\The children of Israel did that which was evil in the sight of Yahweh, and served the Baals;UÌand they forsook Yahweh, the God of their fathers, who brought them out of the land of Egypt, and followed other gods, of the gods of the peoples who were around them, and bowed themselves down to them: and they provoked Yahweh to anger.U7They forsook Yahweh, and served Baal and the Ashtaroth.UÔThe anger of Yahweh was kindled against Israel, and he delivered them into the hands of spoilers who despoiled them; and he sold them into the hands of their enemies all around, so that they could not any longer stand before their enemies.UõWherever they went out, the hand of Yahweh was against them for evil, as Yahweh had spoken, and as Yahweh had sworn to them: and they were sore distressed.UTYahweh raised up judges, who saved them out of the hand of those who despoiled them.T␀␀␀Yet they didn't listen to their judges; for they played the prostitute after other gods, and bowed themselves down to them: they turned aside quickly out of the way in which their fathers walked, obeying the commandments of Yahweh; [but] they didn't do so.UˆWhen Yahweh raised them up judges, then Yahweh was with the judge, and saved them out of the hand of their enemies all the days of the judge: for it grieved Yahweh because of their groaning by reason of those who oppressed them and troubled them.UÔBut it happened, when the judge was dead, that they turned back, and dealt more corruptly than their fathers, in following other gods to serve them, and to bow down to them; they didn't cease from their doings, nor from their stubborn way.U≤The anger of Yahweh was kindled against Israel; and he said, Because this nation have transgressed my covenant which I commanded their fathers, and have not listened to my voice;UgI also will not henceforth drive out any from before them of the nations that Joshua left when he died;UÄthat by them I may prove Israel, whether they will keep the way of Yahweh to walk therein, as their fathers did keep it, or not.UrSo Yahweh left those nations, without driving them out hastily; neither delivered he them into the hand of Joshua.t(NUáNow these are the nations which Yahweh left, to prove Israel by them, even as many [of Israel] as had not known all the wars of Canaan;UÇonly that the generations of the children of Israel might know, to teach them war, at the least such as before knew nothing of it:Uµ[namely], the five lords of the Philistines, and all the Canaanites, and the Sidonians, and the Hivites who lived on Mount Lebanon, from Mount Baal Hermon to the entrance of Hamath.UñThey were [left], to prove Israel by them, to know whether they would listen to the commandments of Yahweh, which he commanded their fathers by Moses.UäThe children of Israel lived among the Canaanites, the Hittites, and the Amorites, and the Perizzites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites:Urand they took their daughters to be their wives, and gave their own daughters to their sons and served their gods.UäThe children of Israel did that which was evil in the sight of Yahweh, and forgot Yahweh their God, and served the Baals and the Asheroth.U√Therefore the anger of Yahweh was kindled against Israel, and he sold them into the hand of Cushan Rishathaim king of Mesopotamia: and the children of Israel served Cushan Rishathaim eight years.U©When the children of Israel cried to Yahweh, Yahweh raised up a savior to the children of Israel, who saved them, even Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb's younger brother.UÀThe Spirit of Yahweh came on him, and he judged Israel; and he went out to war, and Yahweh delivered Cushan Rishathaim king of Mesopotamia into his hand: and his hand prevailed against Cushan Rishathaim.U=The land had rest forty years. Othniel the son of Kenaz died.UÕThe children of Israel again did that which was evil in the sight of Yahweh: and Yahweh strengthened Eglon the king of Moab against Israel, because they had done that which was evil in the sight of Yahweh.U~He gathered to him the children of Ammon and Amalek; and he went and struck Israel, and they possessed the city of palm trees.UDThe children of Israel served Eglon the king of Moab eighteen years.UŒBut when the children of Israel cried to Yahweh, Yahweh raised them up a savior, Ehud the son of Gera, the Benjamite, a man left-handed. The children of Israel sent tribute by him to Eglon the king of Moab.UuEhud made him a sword which had two edges, a cubit in length; and he girded it under his clothing on his right thigh.UKHe offered the tribute to Eglon