d to Barak, Up; for this is the day in which Yahweh has delivered Sisera into your hand; hasn't Yahweh gone out before you? So Barak went down from Mount Tabor, and ten thousand men after him.U©Yahweh confused Sisera, and all his chariots, and all his army, with the edge of the sword before Barak; and Sisera alighted from his chariot, and fled away on his feet.U´But Barak pursued after the chariots, and after the army, to Harosheth of the Gentiles: and all the army of Sisera fell by the edge of the sword; there was not a man left.U≠However Sisera fled away on his feet to the tent of Jael the wife of Heber the Kenite; for there was peace between Jabin the king of Hazor and the house of Heber the Kenite.U°Jael went out to meet Sisera, and said to him, Turn in, my lord, turn in to me; don't be afraid. He came in to her into the tent, and she covered him with a rug.UãHe said to her, Please give me a little water to drink; for I am thirsty. She opened a bottle of milk, and gave him drink, and covered him.U¢He said to her, Stand in the door of the tent, and it shall be, when any man does come and inquire of you, and say, Is there any man here? that you shall say, No.UﬂThen Jael Heber's wife took a tent peg, and took a hammer in her hand, and went softly to him, and struck the pin into his temples, and it pierced through into the ground; for he was in a deep sleep; so he swooned and died.UœBehold, as Barak pursued Sisera, Jael came out to meet him, and said to him, Come, and I will show you the man whom you seek. He came to her; and behold, Sisera lay dead, and the tent peg was in his temples.URSo God subdued on that day Jabin the king of Canaan before the children of Israel.UãThe hand of the children of Israel prevailed more and more against Jabin the king of Canaan, until they had destroyed Jabin king of Canaan.t(NUCThen Deborah and Barak the son of Abinoam sang on that day, saying,UqBecause the leaders took the lead in Israel, because the people offered themselves willingly, be blessed, Yahweh!UzHear, you kings! Give ear, you princes! I, [even] I, will sing to Yahweh. I will sing praise to Yahweh, the God of Israel.UúYahweh, when you went forth out of Seir, when you marched out of the field of Edom, the earth trembled, the sky also dropped. Yes, the clouds dropped water.UiThe mountains quaked at the presence of Yahweh, even Sinai, at the presence of Yahweh, the God of Israel.UÄIn the days of Shamgar the son of Anath, in the days of Jael, the highways were unoccupied. The travelers walked through byways.UcThe rulers ceased in Israel. They ceased until I, Deborah, arose; Until I arose a mother in Israel.UpThey chose new gods. Then war was in the gates. Was there a shield or spear seen among forty thousand in Israel?UlMy heart is toward the governors of Israel, who offered themselves willingly among the people. Bless Yahweh!UfTell [of it], you who ride on white donkeys, you who sit on rich carpets, and you who walk by the way.UÿFar from the noise of archers, in the places of drawing water, there they will rehearse the righteous acts of Yahweh, [Even] the righteous acts of his rule in Israel. Then the people of Yahweh went down to the gates.UqAwake, awake, Deborah! Awake, awake, utter a song! Arise, Barak, and lead away your captives, you son of Abinoam.UdThen a remnant of the nobles [and] the people came down. Yahweh came down for me against the mighty.U∏Those whose root is in Amalek came out of Ephraim, after you, Benjamin, among your peoples. Governors come down out of Machir. Those who handle the marshal's staff came out of Zebulun.UµThe princes of Issachar were with Deborah. As was Issachar, so was Barak. They rushed into the valley at his feet. By the watercourses of Reuben, there were great resolves of heart.UèWhy did you sit among the sheepfolds, To hear the whistling for the flocks? At the watercourses of Reuben There were great searchings of heart.U~Gilead lived beyond the Jordan. Why did Dan remain in ships? Asher sat still