srael grant your petition that you have asked of him.UàShe said, Let your handmaid find favor in your sight. So the woman went her way, and ate; and her facial expression wasn't sad any more.U¨They rose up in the morning early, and worshiped before Yahweh, and returned, and came to their house to Ramah: and Elkanah knew Hannah his wife; and Yahweh remembered her.UôIt happened, when the time was come about, that Hannah conceived, and bore a son; and she named him Samuel, [saying], Because I have asked him of Yahweh.UaThe man Elkanah, and all his house, went up to offer to Yahweh the yearly sacrifice, and his vow.UπBut Hannah didn't go up; for she said to her husband, [I will not go up] until the child be weaned; and then I will bring him, that he may appear before Yahweh, and there abide forever.U∂Elkanah her husband said to her, Do what seems you good; wait until you have weaned him; only Yahweh establish his word. So the woman waited and nursed her son, until she weaned him.UºWhen she had weaned him, she took him up with her, with three bulls, and one ephah of meal, and a bottle of wine, and brought him to the house of Yahweh in Shiloh: and the child was young.U3They killed the bull, and brought the child to Eli.UlShe said, Oh, my lord, as your soul lives, my lord, I am the woman who stood by you here, praying to Yahweh.URFor this child I prayed; and Yahweh has given me my petition which I asked of him:Uttherefore also I have granted him to Yahweh; as long as he lives he is granted to Yahweh. He worshiped Yahweh there.t(NUúHannah prayed, and said: My heart exults in Yahweh! My horn is exalted in Yahweh. My mouth is enlarged over my enemies, because I rejoice in your salvation.UgThere is no one as holy as Yahweh, For there is no one besides you, nor is there any rock like our God.UåTalk no more so exceeding proudly. Don't let arrogance come out of your mouth, For Yahweh is a God of knowledge. By him actions are weighed.USThe bows of the mighty men are broken. Those 