e three men going up to God to Bethel, one carrying three kids, and another carrying three loaves of bread, and another carrying a bottle of wine:Uaand they will greet you, and give you two loaves of bread, which you shall receive of their hand.T>␀␀After that you shall come to the hill of God, where is the garrison of the Philistines: and it shall happen, when you are come there to the city, that you shall meet a band of prophets coming down from the high place with a psaltery, and a tambourine, and a pipe, and a harp, before them; and they will be prophesying:U{and the Spirit of Yahweh will come mightily on you, and you shall prophesy with them, and shall be turned into another man.UjLet it be, when these signs are come to you, that you do as occasion shall serve you; for God is with you.UÂYou shall go down before me to Gilgal; and behold, I will come down to you, to offer burnt offerings, and to sacrifice sacrifices of peace offerings: you shall wait seven days, until I come to you, and show you what you shall do.UÅIt was so, that when he had turned his back to go from Samuel, God gave him another heart: and all those signs happened that day.UèWhen they came there to the hill, behold, a band of prophets met him; and the Spirit of God came mightily on him, and he prophesied among them.U–It happened, when all who knew him before saw that, behold, he prophesied with the prophets, then the people said one to another, What is this that is come to the son of Kish? Is Saul also among the prophets?UtOne of the same place answered, Who is their father? Therefore it became a proverb, Is Saul also among the prophets?UBWhen he had made an end of prophesying, he came to the high place.UóSaul's uncle said to him and to his servant, Where went you? He said, To seek the donkeys; and when we saw that they were not found, we came to Samuel.U<Saul's uncle said, Tell me, Please, what Samuel said to you.UúSaul said to his uncle, He told us plainly that the donkeys were found. But concerning the matter of the kingdom, of which Samuel spoke, he didn't tell him.U6Samuel called the people together to Yahweh to Mizpah;Uﬂand he said to the children of Israel, Thus says Yahweh, the God of Israel, I brought up Israel out of Egypt, and I delivered you out of the hand of the Egyptians, and out of the hand of all the kingdoms that oppressed you:U¸but you have this day rejected your God, who himself saves you out of all your calamities and your distresses; and you have said to him, [No], but set a king over us. Now therefore present yourselves before Yahweh by your tribes, and by your thousands.UUSo Samuel brought all the tribes of Israel near, and the tribe of Benjamin was taken.U∑He brought the tribe of Benjamin near by their families; and the family of the Matrites was taken; and Saul the son of Kish was taken: but when they sought him, he could not be found.UáTherefore they asked of Yahweh further, Is there yet a man to come here? Yahweh answered, Behold, he has hid himself among the baggage.UáThey ran and fetched him there; and when he stood among the people, he was higher than any of the people from his shoulders and upward.UÆSamuel said to all the people, "You see him whom Yahweh has chosen, that there is none like him among all the people?" All the people shouted, and said, [Long] live the king.U•Then Samuel told the people the manner of the kingdom, and wrote it in a book, and laid it up before Yahweh. Samuel sent all the people away, every man to his house.UfSaul also went to his house to Gibeah; and there went with him the army, whose hearts God had touched.UÖBut certain worthless fellows said, How shall this man save us? They despised him, and brought him no present. But he held his peace.t(NUüThen Nahash the Ammonite came up, and encamped against Jabesh Gilead: and all the men of Jabesh said to Nahash, Make a covenant with us, and we will serve you.U°Nahash the Ammonite said to them, On this condition will I make it with you, that all your right eyes be put out; and I will lay it for a reproach on all Israel.U∏The elders of Jabesh said to him, Give us seven days' respite, that we may send messengers to all the borders of Israel; and then, if there be none to save us, we will come out to you.UêThen came the messengers to Gibeah of Saul, and spoke these words in the ears of the people: and all the people lifted up their voice, and wept.UòBehold, Saul came following the oxen out of the field; and Saul said, What ails the people that they weep? They told him the words of the men of Jabesh.UeThe Spirit of God came mightily on Saul when he heard those words, and his anger was kindled greatly.T$␀␀He took a yoke of oxen, and cut them in pieces, and sent them throughout all the borders of Israel by the hand of messengers, saying, Whoever doesn't come forth after Saul and after Samuel, so shall it be done to his oxen. The dread of Yahweh fell on the people, and they came out as one man.UxHe numbered them in Bezek; and the children of Israel were three hundred thousand, and the men of Judah thirty thousand.UŸThey said to the messengers who came, Thus you shall tell the men of Jabesh Gilead, Tomorrow, by the time the sun is hot, you shall have deliverance. The messengers came and told the men of Jabesh; and they were glad.UxTherefore the men of Jabesh said, Tomorrow we will come out to you, and you shall do with us all that seems good to you.T␀␀It was so on the next day, that Saul put the people in three companies; and they came into the midst of the camp in the morning watch, and struck the Ammonites until the heat of the day: and it happened, that those who remained were scattered, so that no two of them were left together.UvThe people said to Samuel, Who is he who said, Shall Saul reign over us? bring the men, that we may put them to death.UmSaul said, There shall not a man be put to death this day; for today Yahweh has worked deliverance in Israel.U[Then said Samuel to the people, Come, and let us go to Gilgal, and renew the kingdom there.U‘All the people went to Gilgal; and there they made Saul king before Yahweh in Gilgal; and there they offered sacrifices of peace offerings before Yahweh; and there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly.t(NU{Samuel said to all Israel, Behold, I have listened to your voice in all that you said to me, and have made a king over you.UüNow, behold, the king walks before you; and I am old and gray-headed; and behold, my sons are with you: and I have walked before you from my youth to this day.T	␀␀Here I am: witness against me before Yahweh, and before his anointed: whose ox have I taken? or whose donkey have I taken? or whom have I defrauded? whom have I oppressed? or of whose hand have I taken a ransom to blind my eyes therewith? and I will restore it you.UjThey said, You have not defrauded us, nor oppressed us, neither have you taken anything of any man's hand.UúHe said to them, Yahweh is witness against you, and his anointed is witness this day, that you have not found anything in my hand. They said, He is witness.UÅSamuel said to the people, It is Yahweh who appointed Moses and Aaron, and that brought your fathers up out of the land of Egypt.UòNow therefore stand still, that I may plead with you before Yahweh concerning all the righteous acts of Yahweh, which he did to you and to your fathers.U∂When Jacob was come into Egypt, and your fathers cried to Yahweh, then Yahweh sent Moses and Aaron, who brought forth your fathers out of Egypt, and made them to dwell in this place.U‘But they forgot Yahweh their God; and he sold them into the hand of Sisera, captain of the army of Hazor, and into the hand of the Philistines, and into the hand of the king of Moab; and they fought against them.U«They cried to Yahweh, and said, We have sinned, because we have forsaken Yahweh, and have served the Baals and the Ashtaroth: but now deliver us out of the hand of our enemies, and we will serve you.UïYahweh sent Jerubbaal, and Bedan, and Jephth