ife in his hand, and struck the Philistine, and Yahweh worked a great victory for all Israel: you saw it, and did rejoice; why then will you sin against innocent blood, to kill David without a cause?UfSaul listened to the voice of Jonathan: and Saul swore, As Yahweh lives, he shall not be put to death.UáJonathan called David, and Jonathan showed him all those things. Jonathan brought David to Saul, and he was in his presence, as before.UãThere was war again: and David went out, and fought with the Philistines, and killed them with a great slaughter; and they fled before him.UAn evil spirit from Yahweh was on Saul, as he sat in his house with his spear in his hand; and David was playing with his hand.U∑Saul sought to strike David even to the wall with the spear; but he slipped away out of Saul's presence, and he struck the spear into the wall: and David fled, and escaped that night.U¡Saul sent messengers to David's house, to watch him, and to kill him in the morning: and Michal, David's wife, told him, saying, If you don't save your life tonight, tomorrow you will be slain.UPSo Michal let David down through the window: and he went, and fled, and escaped.UÅMichal took the teraphim, and laid it in the bed, and put a pillow of goats' [hair] at its head, and covered it with the clothes.U>When Saul sent messengers to take David, she said, He is sick.UbSaul sent the messengers to see David, saying, Bring him up to me in the bed, that I may kill him.UoWhen the messengers came in, behold, the teraphim was in the bed, with the pillow of goats' [hair] at its head.U¶Saul said to Michal, Why have you deceived me thus, and let my enemy go, so that he is escaped? Michal answered Saul, He said to me, Let me go; why should I kill you?UçNow David fled, and escaped, and came to Samuel to Ramah, and told him all that Saul had done to him. He and Samuel went and lived in Naioth.U>It was told Saul, saying, Behold, David is at Naioth in Ramah.U—Saul sent messengers to take David: and whe