t know her intimately.UïThen Adonijah the son of Haggith exalted himself, saying, I will be king: and he prepared him chariots and horsemen, and fifty men to run before him.UêHis father had not displeased him at any time in saying, Why have you done so? and he was also a very goodly man; and he was born after Absalom.UpHe conferred with Joab the son of Zeruiah, and with Abiathar the priest: and they following Adonijah helped him.U•But Zadok the priest, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and Nathan the prophet, and Shimei, and Rei, and the mighty men who belonged to David, were not with Adonijah.U¡Adonijah killed sheep and cattle and fatlings by the stone of Zoheleth, which is beside En Rogel; and he called all his brothers, the king's sons, and all the men of Judah, the king's servants:Uabut Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah, and the mighty men, and Solomon his brother, he didn't call.UúThen Nathan spoke to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon, saying, Haven't you heard that Adonijah the son of Haggith reigns, and David our lord doesn't know it?UvNow therefore come, please let me give you counsel, that you may save your own life, and the life of your son Solomon.U◊Go and get you in to king David, and tell him, Didn't you, my lord, king, swear to your handmaid, saying, Assuredly Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne? why then does Adonijah reign?UfBehold, while you yet talk there with the king, I also will come in after you, and confirm your words.UÇBathsheba went in to the king into the chamber: and the king was very old; and Abishag the Shunammite was ministering to the king.UNBathsheba bowed, and did obeisance to the king. The king said, What would you?U¢She said to him, My lord, you swore by Yahweh your God to your handmaid, [saying], Assuredly Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne.UGNow, behold, Adonijah reigns; and you, my lord the king, don't know it:UÀand he has slain cattle and fatlings and sheep in abundance, and has called all the sons of the king, and Abiathar the priest, and Joab the captain of the army; but he hasn't called Solomon your servant.UéYou, my lord the king, the eyes of all Israel are on you, that you should tell them who shall sit on the throne of my lord the king after him.UÉOtherwise it will happen, when my lord the king shall sleep with his fathers, that I and my son Solomon shall be counted offenders.UGBehold, while she yet talked with the king, Nathan the prophet came in.UöThey told the king, saying, Behold, Nathan the prophet. When he was come in before the king, he bowed himself before the king with his face to the ground.UhNathan said, My lord, king, have you said, Adonijah shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne?T␀␀For he is gone down this day, and has slain cattle and fatlings and sheep in abundance, and has called all the king's sons, and the captains of the army, and Abiathar the priest; and behold, they are eating and drinking before him, and say, [Long] live king Adonijah.UBut he hasn't called me, even me your servant, and Zadok the priest, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and your servant Solomon.UäIs this thing done by my lord the king, and you haven't shown to your servants who should sit on the throne of my lord the king after him?UmThen king David answered, Call to me Bathsheba. She came into the king's presence, and stood before the king.UYThe king swore, and said, As Yahweh lives, who has redeemed my soul out of all adversity,U»most certainly as I swore to you by Yahweh, the God of Israel, saying, Assuredly Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne in my place; most certainly so will I do this day.U~Then Bathsheba bowed with her face to the earth, and did obeisance to the king, and said, Let my lord king David live forever.UÅKing David said, Call to me Zadok the priest, and Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada. They came before the king.UçThe king said to them, Take with yo