 twentieth year of Jotham the son of Uzziah.UÜNow the rest of the acts of Pekah, and all that he did, behold, they are written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel.UuIn the second year of Pekah the son of Remaliah king of Israel began Jotham the son of Uzziah king of Judah to reign.UòHe was twenty-five years old when he began to reign; and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem: and his mother's name was Jerusha the daughter of Zadok.UkHe did that which was right in the eyes of Yahweh; he did according to all that his father Uzziah had done.UüHowever the high places were not taken away: the people still sacrificed and burned incense in the high places. He built the upper gate of the house of Yahweh.UÅNow the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all that he did, aren't they written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah?UhIn those days Yahweh began to send against Judah Rezin the king of Syria, and Pekah the son of Remaliah.UÜJotham slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in the city of David his father: and Ahaz his son reigned in his place.t(NUiIn the seventeenth year of Pekah the son of Remaliah Ahaz the son of Jotham king of Judah began to reign.U∏Twenty years old was Ahaz when he began to reign; and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem: and he didn't do that which was right in the eyes of Yahweh his God, like David his father.U«But he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, yes, and made his son to pass through the fire, according to the abominations of the nations, whom Yahweh cast out from before the children of Israel.UaHe sacrificed and burnt incense in the high places, and on the hills, and under every green tree.UíThen Rezin king of Syria and Pekah son of Remaliah king of Israel came up to Jerusalem to war: and they besieged Ahaz, but could not overcome him.UñAt that time Rezin king of Syria recovered Elath to Syria, and drove the Jews from Elath; and the Syrians came to Elath, and lived there, to this day.U·So Ahaz sent messengers to Tiglath Pileser king of Assyria, saying, I am your servant and your son: come up, and save me out of the hand of the king of Syria, and out of the hand of the king of Israel, who rise up against me.U†Ahaz took the silver and gold that was found in the house of Yahweh, and in the treasures of the king's house, and sent it for a present to the king of Assyria.U§The king of Assyria listened to him; and the king of Assyria went up against Damascus, and took it, and carried [the people of] it captive to Kir, and killed Rezin.U‡King Ahaz went to Damascus to meet Tiglath Pileser king of Assyria, and saw the altar that was at Damascus; and king Ahaz sent to Urijah the priest the fashion of the altar, and its pattern, according to all its workmanship.U©Urijah the priest built an altar: according to all that king Ahaz had sent from Damascus, so did Urijah the priest make it against the coming of king Ahaz from Damascus.UwWhen the king was come from Damascus, the king saw the altar: and the king drew near to the altar, and offered thereon.UèHe burnt his burnt offering and his meal offering, and poured his drink offering, and sprinkled the blood of his peace offerings, on the altar.U±The bronze altar, which was before Yahweh, he brought from the forefront of the house, from between his altar and the house of Yahweh, and put it on the north side of his altar.T≤␀␀King Ahaz commanded Urijah the priest, saying, On the great altar burn the morning burnt offering, and the evening meal offering, and the king's burnt offering, and his meal offering, with the burnt offering of all the people of the land, and their meal offering, and their drink offerings; and sprinkle on it all the blood of the burnt offering, and all the blood of the sacrifice: but the bronze altar shall be for me to inquire by.UDUrijah the priest did so, according to all that king Ahaz commanded.UµKing Ahaz cut off the panels of the bases, and removed the basin from off them, and took down the sea from off the bronze oxen that were under it, and put it on a pavement of stone.U°The covered way for the Sabbath that they had built in the house, and the king's entry outside, turned he to the house of Yahweh, because of the king of Assyria.UwNow the rest of the acts of Ahaz which he did, aren't they written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah?U}Ahaz slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in the city of David: and Hezekiah his son reigned in his place.t(NUÅIn the twelfth year of Ahaz king of Judah began Hoshea the son of Elah to reign in Samaria over Israel, [and reigned] nine years.UfHe did that which was evil in the sight of Yahweh, yet not as the kings of Israel who were before him.UhAgainst him came up Shalmaneser king of Assyria; and Hoshea became his servant, and brought him tribute.UÔThe king of Assyria found conspiracy in Hoshea; for he had sent messengers to So king of Egypt, and offered no tribute to the king of Assyria, as he had done year by year: therefore the king of Assyria shut him up, and bound him in prison.UnThen the king of Assyria came up throughout all the land, and went up to Samaria, and besieged it three years.U¡In the ninth year of Hoshea the king of Assyria took Samaria, and carried Israel away to Assyria, and placed them in Halah, and on the Habor, the river of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes.UƒIt was so, because the children of Israel had sinned against Yahweh their God, who brought them up out of the land of Egypt from under the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt, and had feared other gods,Uêand walked in the statutes of the nations, whom Yahweh cast out from before the children of Israel, and of the kings of Israel, which they made.U√The children of Israel did secretly things that were not right against Yahweh their God: and they built them high places in all their cities, from the tower of the watchmen to the fortified city;UXand they set them up pillars and Asherim on every high hill, and under every green tree;Ußand there they burnt incense in all the high places, as did the nations whom Yahweh carried away before them; and they worked wicked things to provoke Yahweh to anger;UUand they served idols, of which Yahweh had said to them, You shall not do this thing.T␀␀Yet Yahweh testified to Israel, and to Judah, by every prophet, and every seer, saying, Turn you from your evil ways, and keep my commandments and my statutes, according to all the law which I commanded your fathers, and which I sent to you by my servants the prophets.UÜNotwithstanding, they would not hear, but hardened their neck, like the neck of their fathers, who didn't believe in Yahweh their God.T)␀␀They rejected his statutes, and his covenant that he made with their fathers, and his testimonies which he testified to them; and they followed vanity, and became vain, and [went] after the nations that were around them, concerning whom Yahweh had commanded them that they should not do like them.U±They forsook all the commandments of Yahweh their God, and made them molten images, even two calves, and made an Asherah, and worshiped all the army of the sky, and served Baal.U…They caused their sons and their daughters to pass through the fire, and used divination and enchantments, and sold themselves to do that which was evil in the sight of Yahweh, to provoke him to anger.UÄTherefore Yahweh was very angry with Israel, and removed them out of his sight: there was none left but the tribe of Judah only.UrAlso Judah didn't keep the commandments of Yahweh their God, but walked in the statutes of Israel which they made.UíYahweh rejected all the seed of Israel, and afflicted them, and delivered them into the hand of spoilers, until he had cast them out of his sight.U©For he tore Israel from the house of David; and they made Jeroboam the son of Nebat king: and Jeroboam drove Israel from following Yahweh, and made them sin a great sin.UeThe children of Israel walked in all the sins of Jeroboam which he did; they didn't depart from them;U§until Yahweh removed Israel out of his sight, as he spoke by all his servants the prophets. So Israel was carried away out of their own land to Assyria to this day.UÙThe king of Assyria brought men from Babylon, and from Cuthah, and from Avva, and from Hamath and Sepharvaim, and placed them in the cities of Samaria instead of the children of Israel; and they possessed Samaria, and lived in the cities of it.UïSo it was, at the beginning of their dwelling there, that they didn't fear Yahweh: therefore Yahweh sent lions among them, which killed some of them.T)␀␀Therefore they spoke to the king of Assyria, saying, The nations which you have carried away, and placed in the cities of Samaria, don't know the law of the god of the land: therefore he has sent lions among them, and behold, they kill them, because they don't know the law of the god of the land.UøThen the king of Assyria commanded, saying, Carry there one of the priests whom you brought from there; and let them go and dwell there, and let him teach them the law of the god of the land.UÑSo one of the priests whom they had carried away from Samaria came and lived in Bethel, and taught them how they should fear Yahweh.U´However every nation made gods of their own, and put them in the houses of the high places which the Samaritans had made, every nation in their cities in which they lived.UkThe men of Babylon made Succoth Benoth, and the men of Cuth made Nergal, and the men of Hamath made Ashima,Uìand the Avvites made Nibhaz and Tartak; and the Sepharvites burnt their children in the fire to Adrammelech and Anammelech, the gods of Sepharvaim.UìSo they feared Yahweh, and made to them from among themselves priests of the high places, who sacrificed for them in the houses of the high places.UzThey feared Yahweh, and served their own gods, after the manner of the nations from among whom they had been carried away.UÛTo this day they do after the former manner: they don't fear Yahweh, 