e son of Abiathar, were priests; and Shavsha was scribe;U}and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites; and the sons of David were chief about the king.t(NUmIt happened after this, that Nahash the king of the children of Ammon died, and his son reigned in his place.U¸David said, I will show kindness to Hanun the son of Nahash, because his father showed kindness to me. So David sent messengers to comfort him concerning his father. David's servants came into the land of the children of Ammon to Hanun, to comfort him.U·But the princes of the children of Ammon said to Hanun, Think you that David does honor your father, in that he has sent comforters to you? Aren't his servants come to you to search, and to overthrow, and to spy out the land?UÜSo Hanun took David's servants, and shaved them, and cut off their garments in the middle, even to their buttocks, and sent them away.UÕThen there went certain persons, and told David how the men were served. He sent to meet them; for the men were greatly ashamed. The king said, Stay at Jericho until your beards are grown, and then return.UÒWhen the children of Ammon saw that they had made themselves odious to David, Hanun and the children of Ammon sent one thousand talents of silver to hire them chariots and horsemen out of Mesopotamia, and out of Arammaacah, and out of Zobah.U÷So they hired them thirty-two thousand chariots, and the king of Maacah and his people, who came and encamped before Medeba. The children of Ammon gathered themselves together from their cities, and came to battle.UIWhen David heard of it, he sent Joab, and all the army of the mighty men.UêThe children of Ammon came out, and put the battle in array at the gate of the city: and the kings who had come were by themselves in the field.UùNow when Joab saw that the battle was set against him before and behind, he chose of all the choice men of Israel, and put them in array against the Syrians.UâThe rest of the people he committed in