l bow toward your holy temple in reverence of you.UdLead me, Yahweh, in your righteousness because of my enemies. Make your way straight before my face.UÜFor there is no faithfulness in their mouth. Their heart is destruction. Their throat is an open tomb. They flatter with their tongue.UôHold them guilty, God. Let them fall by their own counsels; Thrust them out in the multitude of their transgressions, for they have rebelled against you.UúBut let all those who take refuge in you rejoice, Let them always shout for joy, because you defend them. Let them also who love your name be joyful in you.U\For you will bless the righteous. Yahweh, you will surround him with favor as with a shield.t(Ub[For the Chief Musician; on stringed instruments, upon the eight-stringed lyre. A Psalm by David.]UKYahweh, don't rebuke me in your anger, neither discipline me in your wrath.UUHave mercy on me, Yahweh, for I am faint. Yahweh, heal me, for my bones are troubled.U<My soul is also in great anguish. But you, Yahweh--how long?ULReturn, Yahweh. Deliver my soul, and save me for your loving kindness' sake.ULFor in death there is no memory of you. In Sheol, who shall give you thanks?UYI am weary with my groaning. Every night I flood my bed. I drench my couch with my tears.UPMy eye wastes away because of grief. It grows old because of all my adversaries.UZDepart from me, all you workers of iniquity, for Yahweh has heard the voice of my weeping.U;Yahweh has heard my supplication. Yahweh accepts my prayer.UcMay all my enemies be ashamed and dismayed. They shall turn back, they shall be disgraced suddenly.t(U^[A meditation by David, which he sang to Yahweh, concerning the words of Cush, the Benjamite.]U[Yahweh, my God, I take refuge in you. Save me from all those who pursue me, and deliver me,U_lest they tear apart my soul like a lion, ripping it in pieces, while there is none to deliver.UFYahweh, my God, if I have done this, if there is iniquity in my hands,Uzif I have rewarded evil to him w