d to be insane before Abimelech, who drove him away, and he departed.Psalm 34 is an acrostic poem, with each verse starting with a letter of the alphabet (ordered from Alef to Tav).]UHI will bless Yahweh at all times. His praise will always be in my mouth.UHMy soul shall boast in Yahweh. The humble shall hear of it, and be glad.U:Oh magnify Yahweh with me. Let us exalt his name together.UHI sought Yahweh, and he answered me, and delivered me from all my fears.UTThey looked to him, and were radiant. Their faces shall never be covered with shame.UQThis poor man cried, and Yahweh heard him, and saved him out of all his troubles.UIThe angel of Yahweh encamps around those who fear him, and delivers them.UQOh taste and see that Yahweh is good. Blessed is the man who takes refuge in him.UMOh fear Yahweh, you his saints, for there is no lack with those who fear him.UdThe young lions do lack, and suffer hunger, but those who seek Yahweh shall not lack any good thing.UFCome, you children, listen to me. I will teach you the fear of Yahweh.UKWho is someone who desires life, and loves many days, that he may see good?U=Keep your tongue from evil, and your lips from speaking lies.U9Depart from evil, and do good. seek peace, and pursue it.UEYahweh's eyes are toward the righteous. His ears listen to their cry.UYYahweh's face is against those who do evil, to cut off the memory of them from the earth.UQThe righteous cry, and Yahweh hears, and delivers them out of all their troubles.U[Yahweh is near to those who have a broken heart, and saves those who have a crushed spirit.USMany are the afflictions of the righteous, but Yahweh delivers him out of them all.U8He protects all of his bones. Not one of them is broken.ULEvil shall kill the wicked. Those who hate the righteous shall be condemned.UaYahweh redeems the soul of his servants. None of those who take refuge in him shall be condemned.t(U[By David.]UZContend, Yahweh, with those who contend with me. Fight against those who fight against me.U:Take hold of shield and buckler, and stand up for my help.UVBrandish the spear and block those who pursue me. Tell my soul, "I am your salvation."UÉLet those who seek after my soul be disappointed and brought to dishonor. Let those who plot my ruin be turned back and confounded.UELet them be as chaff before the wind, Yahweh's angel driving them on.UALet their way be dark and slippery, Yahweh's angel pursuing them.UlFor without cause they have hidden their net in a pit for me. Without cause they have dug a pit for my soul.UwLet destruction come on him unawares. Let his net that he has hidden catch himself. Let him fall into that destruction.UEMy soul shall be joyful in Yahweh. It shall rejoice in his salvation.UüAll my bones shall say, "Yahweh, who is like you, who delivers the poor from him who is too strong for him; yes, the poor and the needy from him who robs him?"UPUnrighteous witnesses rise up. They ask me about things that I don't know about.U:They reward me evil for good, to the bereaving of my soul.UÜBut as for me, when they were sick, my clothing was sackcloth. I afflicted my soul with fasting. My prayer returned into my own bosom.UtI behaved myself as though it had been my friend or my brother. I bowed down mourning, as one who mourns his mother.UµBut in my adversity, they rejoiced, and gathered themselves together. The attackers gathered themselves together against me, and I didn't know it. They tore at me, and didn't cease.UCLike the profane mockers in feasts, they gnashed their teeth at me.UhLord, how long will you look on? Rescue my soul from their destruction, my precious life from the lions.URI will give you thanks in the great assembly. I will praise you among many people.U}Don't let those who are my enemies wrongfully rejoice over me; neither let those who hate me without a cause wink their eyes.UdFor they don't speak peace, but they devise deceitful words against those who are quiet in the land.UYYes, they opened their mouth wide against me. They said, "Aha! Aha! Our eye has seen it!"UHYou have seen it, Yahweh. Don't keep silent. Lord, don't be far from me.U?Wake up! Rise up to defend me, my God! My Lord, contend for me!U[Vindicate me, Yahweh my God, according to your righteousness. Don't let them gloat over me.UtDon't let them say in their heart, "Aha! That's the way we want it!" Don't let them say, "We have swallowed him up!"UõLet them be disappointed and confounded together who rejoice at my calamity. Let them be clothed with shame and dishonor who magnify themselves against me.U™Let them shout for joy and be glad, who favor my righteous cause. Yes, let them say continually, "Yahweh be magnified, who has pleasure in the prosperity of his servant!"UQMy tongue shall talk about your righteousness and about your praise all day long.t(U:[For the Chief Musician. By David, the servant of Yahweh.]UmAn oracle is within my heart about the disobedience of the wicked: "There is no fear of God before his eyes."UMFor he flatters himself in his own eyes, too much to detect and hate his sin.UXThe words of his mouth are iniquity and deceit. He has ceased to be wise and to do good.U_He plots iniquity on his bed. He sets himself in a way that is not good. He doesn't abhor evil.UXYour loving kindness, Yahweh, is in the heavens. Your faithfulness reaches to the skies.U{Your righteousness is like the mountains of God. Your judgments are like a great deep. Yahweh, you preserve man and animal.UjHow precious is your loving kindness, God! The children of men take refuge under the shadow of your wings.U}They shall be abundantly satisfied with the abundance of your house. You will make them drink of the river of your pleasures.UEFor with you is the spring of life. In your light shall we see light.UcOh continue your loving kindness to those who know you, your righteousness to the upright in heart.U\Don't let the foot of pride come against me. Don't let the hand of the wicked drive me away.U^There the workers of iniquity are