y head. As a heavy burden, they are too heavy for me.U?My wounds are loathsome and corrupt, because of my foolishness.U?I am pained and bowed down greatly. I go mourning all day long.UGFor my waist is filled with burning. There is no soundness in my flesh.UUI am faint and severely bruised. I have groaned by reason of the anguish of my heart.UFLord, all my desire is before you. My groaning is not hidden from you.UXMy heart throbs. My strength fails me. As for the light of my eyes, it has also left me.UOMy lovers and my friends stand aloof from my plague. My kinsmen stand far away.UÄThey also who seek after my life lay snares. Those who seek my hurt speak mischievous things, and meditate deceits all day long.UPBut I, as a deaf man, don't hear. I am as a mute man who doesn't open his mouth.UDYes, I am as a man who doesn't hear, in whose mouth are no reproofs.U<For in you, Yahweh, do I hope. You will answer, Lord my God.U[For I said, "Don't let them gloat over me, or exalt themselves over me when my foot slips."U9For I am ready to fall. My pain is continually before me.U;For I will declare my iniquity. I will be sorry for my sin.UTBut my enemies are vigorous and many. Those who hate me without reason are numerous.UXThey who also render evil for good are adversaries to me, because I follow what is good.U7Don't forsake me, Yahweh. My God, don't be far from me.U%Hurry to help me, Lord, my salvation.t(U9[For the Chief Musician. For Jeduthun. A Psalm by David.]UÖI said, "I will watch my ways, so that I don't sin with my tongue. I will keep my mouth with a bridle while the wicked is before me."UPI was mute with silence. I held my peace, even from good. My sorrow was stirred.UWMy heart was hot within me. While I meditated, the fire burned: I spoke with my tongue:UT"Yahweh, show me my end, what is the measure of my days. Let me know how frail I am.U~Behold, you have made my days handbreadths. My lifetime is as nothing before you. Surely every man stands as a breath." Selah.U{"Surely every man walks like a shadow. Surely they busy themselves in vain. He heaps up, and doesn't know who shall gather.U1Now, Lord, what do I wait for? My hope is in you.UQDeliver me from all my transgressions. Don't make me the reproach of the foolish.U7I was mute. I didn't open my mouth, because you did it.UIRemove your scourge away from me. I am overcome by the blow of your hand.U{When you rebuke and correct man for iniquity, You consume his wealth like a moth. Surely every man is but a breath." Selah.Uê"Hear my prayer, Yahweh, and give ear to my cry. Don't be silent at my tears. For I am a stranger with you, a foreigner, as all my fathers were.UOOh spare me, that I may recover strength, before I go away, and exist no more."t(U+[For the Chief Musician. A Psalm by David.]UAI waited patiently for Yahweh. He turned to me, and heard my cry.UHe brought me up also out of a horrible pit, out of the miry clay. He set my feet on a rock, and gave me a firm place to stand.UrHe has put a new song in my mouth, even praise to our God. Many shall see it, and fear, and shall trust in Yahweh.UmBlessed is the man who makes Yahweh his trust, and doesn't respect the proud, nor such as turn aside to lies.U◊Many, Yahweh, my God, are the wonderful works which you have done, and your thoughts which are toward us. They can't be declared back to you. If I would declare and speak of them, they are more than can be numbered.UySacrifice and offering you didn't desire. You have opened my ears. You have not required burnt offering and sin offering.UTThen I said, "Behold, I have come. It is written about me in the book in the scroll.UEI delight to do your will, my God. Yes, your law is within my heart."UvI have proclaimed glad news of righteousness in the great assembly. Behold, I will not seal my lips, Yahweh, you know.UΩI have not hidden your righteousness within my heart. I have declared your faithfulness and your salvation. I have not concealed your loving kindness and your truth from the great assembly.UtDon't withhold your tender mercies from me, Yahweh. Let your loving kindness and your truth continually preserve me.U≠For innumerable evils have surrounded me. My iniquities have overtaken me, so that I am not able to look up. They are more than the hairs of my head. My heart has failed me.U<Be pleased, Yahweh, to deliver me. Hurry to help me, Yahweh.U¢Let them be disappointed and confounded together who seek after my soul to destroy it. Let them be turned backward and brought to dishonor who delight in my hurt.UGLet them be desolate by reason of their shame that tell me, "Aha! Aha!"UÄLet all those who seek you rejoice and be glad in you. Let such as love your salvation say continually, "Let Yahweh be exalted!"UlBut I am poor and needy. May the Lord think about me. You are my help and my deliverer. Don't delay, my God.t(U+[For the Chief Musician. A Psalm by David.]UQBlessed is he who considers the poor. Yahweh will deliver him in the day of evil.UâYahweh will preserve him, and keep him alive. He shall be blessed on the earth, and he will not surrender him to the will of his enemies.UPYahweh will sustain him on his sickbed, and restore him from his bed of illness.UKI said, "Yahweh, have mercy on me! Heal me, for I have sinned against you."UJMy enemies speak evil against me: "When will he die, and his name perish?"UsIf he comes to see me, he speaks falsehood. His heart gathers iniquity to itself. When he goes abroad, he tells it.UKAll who hate me whisper together against me. They imagine the worst for me.U\"An evil disease," they say, "has afflicted him. Now that he lies he shall rise up no more."UiYes, my own familiar friend, in whom I trusted, who ate bread with me, has lifted up his heel against me.UJBut you, Yahweh, have mercy on me, and raise me up, that I may repay them.UPBy this I know that you delight in me, because my enemy doesn't triumph over me.UNAs for me, you uphold me in my integrity, and set me in your presence forever.UYBlessed be Yahweh, the God of Israel, from everlasting and to everlasting! Amen and amen.t(U?[For the Chief Musician. A contemplation by the sons of Korah.]UHAs the deer pants for the water brooks, so my soul pants after you, God.UUMy soul thirsts for God, for the living God. When shall I come and appear before God?U]My tears have been my food day and night, while they continually ask me, "Where is your God?"UΩThese things I remember, and pour out my soul within me, how I used to go with the crowd, and led them to the house of God, with the voice of joy and praise, a multitude keeping a holy day.UêWhy are you in despair, my soul? Why are you disturbed within me? Hope in God! For I shall still praise him for the saving help of his presence.UäMy God, my soul is in despair within me. Therefore I remember you from the land of the Jordan, the heights of Hermon, from the hill Mizar.UgDeep calls to deep at the noise of your waterfalls. All your waves and your billows have swept over me.UYahweh will command his loving kindness in the daytime. In the night his song shall be with me: a prayer to the God of my life.UrI will ask God, my rock, "Why have you forgotten me? Why do I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?"UlAs with a sword in my bones, my adversaries reproach me, while they continually ask me, "Where is your God?"UõWhy are you in despair, my soul? Why are you disturbed within me? Hope in God! For I shall still praise him, the saving help of my countenance, and my God.t(NUnVindicate me, God, and plead my cause against an ungodly nation. Oh, deliver me from deceitful and wicked men.UzFor you are the God of my strength. Why have you rejected me? Why do I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?UmOh, send out your light and your truth. Let them lead me. Let them bring me to your holy hill, To your tents.UiThen I will go to the altar of God, to God, my exceeding joy. I will praise you on the harp, God, my God.UéWhy are you in despair, my soul? Why are you disturbed within me? Hope in God! For I shall still praise him: my Savior, my helper, and my God.t(UF[For the Chief Musician. By the sons of Korah. A contemplative psalm.]UpWe have heard with our ears, God; our fathers have told us, what work you did in their days, in the days of old.UvYou drove out the nations with your hand, but you planted them. You afflicted the peoples, but you spread them abroad.U∆For they didn't get the land in possession by their own sword, neither did their own arm save them; but your right hand, and your arm, and the light of your face, because you were favorable to them.U2You are my King, God. Command victories for Jacob!UsThrough you, will we push down our adversaries. Through your name, will we tread them under who rise up against us.U?For I will not trust in my bow, neither shall my sword save me.UNBut you have saved us from our adversaries, and have shamed those who hate us.U\In God we have made our boast all day long, we will give thanks to your name forever. Selah.UVBut now you rejected us, and brought us to dishonor, and don't go out with our armies.UVYou make us turn back from the adversary. Those who hate us take spoil for themselves.UNYou have made us like sheep for food, and have scattered us among the nations.UJYou sell your people for nothing, and have gained nothing from their sale.U^You make us a reproach to our neighbors, a scoffing and a derision to those who are around us.UPYou make us a byword among the nations, a shaking of the head among the peoples.U@All day long my dishonor is before me, and shame covers my face,U]At the taunt of one who reproaches and verbally abuses, because of the enemy and the avenger.UdAll this has come on us, yet have we not forgotten you, Neither have we been false to your covenant.UMOur heart has not turned back, neither have our steps strayed from your path,U\Though you have crushed us in the haunt of jackals, and covered us with the shadow of death.UUIf we have forgotten the name of our God, or spread forth our hands to a strange god;UAwon't God search this out? For he knows the secrets of the heart.UZYes, for your sake we are killed all day long. We are regarded as sheep for the slaughter.U@Wake up! Why do you sleep, Lord? Arise! Don't reject us forever.UHWhy do you hide your face, and forget our affliction and our oppression?UFFor our soul is bowed down to the dust. Our body cleaves to the earth.U=Rise up to help us. Redeem us for your loving kindness' sake.t(Ud[For the Chief Musician. Set to "The Lilies." A contemplation by the sons of Korah. A wedding song.]UwMy heart overflows with a noble theme. I recite my verses for the king. My tongue is like the pen of a skillful writer.UsYou are the most excellent of the sons of men. Grace has anointed your lips, therefore God has blessed you forever.UJGird your sword on your thigh, mighty one: your splendor and your majesty.UÄIn your majesty ride on victoriously on behalf of truth, humility, and righteousness. Let your right hand display awesome deeds.UbYour arrows are sharp. The nations fall under you, with arrows in the heart of the king's enemies.UZYour throne, God, is forever and ever. A scepter of equity is the scepter of your kingdom.UäYou have loved righteousness, and hated wickedness. Therefore God, your God, has anointed you with the oil of gladness above your fellows.UtAll your garments smell like myrrh, aloes, and cassia. Out of ivory palaces stringed instruments have made you glad.UfKings' daughters are among your honorable women. At your right hand the queen stands in gold of Ophir.UdListen, daughter, consider, and turn your ear. Forget your own people, and also your father's house.UDSo the king will desire your beauty, honor him, for he is your lord.UUThe daughter of Tyre comes with a gift. The rich among the people entreat your favor.UJThe princess inside is all glorious. Her clothing is interwoven with gold.UvShe shall be led to the king in embroidered work. The virgins, her companions who follow her, shall be brought to you.UWWith gladness and rejoicing they shall be led. They shall enter into the king's palace.U\Your sons will take the place of your fathers. You shall make them princes in all the earth.U{I will make your name to be remembered in all generations. Therefore the peoples shall give you thanks forever and ever. {}t(U_[For the Chief Musician. By the sons of Korah. According to Alamoth.Alamoth is a musical term.]U?God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble.UsTherefore we won't be afraid, though the earth changes, though the mountains are shaken into the heart of the seas;Uathough its waters roar and are troubled, though the mountains tremble with their swelling. Selah.UoThere is a river, the streams of which make the city of God glad, the holy place of the tents of the Most High.UGGod is in her midst. She shall not be moved. God will help her at dawn.UVThe nations raged. The kingdoms were moved. He lifted his voice, and the earth melted.UCYahweh of Armies is with us. The God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.UDCome, see Yahweh's works, what desolations he has made in the earth.UzHe makes wars cease to the end of the earth. He breaks the bow, and shatters the spear. He burns the chariots in the fire.Uh"Be still, and know that I am God. I will be exalted among the nations. I will be exalted in the earth."UCYahweh of Armies is with us. The God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.t(U7[For the Chief Musician. A Psalm by the sons of Korah.]ULOh clap your hands, all you nations. Shout to God with the voice of triumph!UGFor Yahweh Most High is awesome. He is a great King over all the earth.U8He subdues nations under us, and peoples under our feet.UKHe chooses our inheritance for us, the glory of Jacob whom he loved. Selah.UAGod has gone up with a shout, Yahweh with the sound of a trumpet.UISing praise to God, sing praises. Sing praises to our King, sing praises.UFFor God is the King of all the earth. Sing praises with understanding.U9God 