 life is costly, no payment is ever enough,UBThat he should live on forever, that he should not see corruption.UlFor he sees that wise men die; likewise the fool and the senseless perish, and leave their wealth to others.UîTheir inward thought is that their houses will endure forever, and their dwelling places to all generations. They name their lands after themselves.UPBut man, despite his riches, doesn't endure. He is like the animals that perish.U\This is the destiny of those who are foolish, and of those who approve their sayings. Selah.UºThey are appointed as a flock for Sheol. Death shall be their shepherd. The upright shall have dominion over them in the morning. Their beauty shall decay in Sheol, far from their mansion.USBut God will redeem my soul from the power of Sheol, for he will receive me. Selah.URDon't be afraid when a man is made rich, when the glory of his house is increased.UTFor when he dies he shall carry nothing away. His glory shall not descend after him.U^Though while he lived he blessed his soul-- and men praise you when you do well for yourself--UMhe shall go to the generation of his fathers. They shall never see the light.ULA man who has riches without understanding, is like the animals that perish.t(U[A Psalm by Asaph.]UPThe Mighty One, God, Yahweh, speaks, and calls the earth from sunrise to sunset.U8Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God shines forth.UaOur God comes, and does not keep silent. A fire devours before him. It is very stormy around him.UJHe calls to the heavens above, to the earth, that he may judge his people:UW"Gather my saints together to me, those who have made a covenant with me by sacrifice."UMThe heavens shall declare his righteousness, for God himself is judge. Selah.U_"Hear, my people, and I will speak; Israel, and I will testify against you. I am God, your God.UWI don't rebuke you for your sacrifices. Your burnt offerings are continually before me.UII have no need for a bull from your stall, nor male goats from your pens.UNFor every animal of the forest is mine, and the livestock on a thousand hills.UNI know all the birds of the mountains. The wild animals of the field are mine.UUIf I were hungry, I would not tell you, for the world is mine, and all that is in it.U;Will I eat the flesh of bulls, or drink the blood of goats?UKOffer to God the sacrifice of thanksgiving. Pay your vows to the Most High.UMCall on me in the day of trouble. I will deliver you, and you will honor me."UyBut to the wicked God says, "What right do you have to declare my statutes, that you have taken my covenant on your lips,U;seeing you hate instruction, and throw my words behind you?UTWhen you saw a thief, you consented with him, and have participated with adulterers.U8"You give your mouth to evil. Your tongue frames deceit.UJYou sit and speak against your brother. You slander your own mother's son.UëYou have done these things, and I kept silent. You thought that the I was just like you. I will rebuke you, and accuse you in front of your eyes.Ub"Now consider this, you who forget God, lest I tear you into pieces, and there be none to deliver.U|Whoever offers the sacrifice of thanksgiving glorifies me, and prepares his way so that I will show God's salvation to him."t(Us[For the Chief Musician. A Psalm by David, when Nathan the prophet came to him, after he had gone in to Bathsheba.]UàHave mercy on me, God, according to your loving kindness. According to the multitude of your tender mercies, blot out my transgressions.U<Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity. Cleanse me from my sin.U=For I know my transgressions. My sin is constantly before me.UüAgainst you, and you only, have I sinned, and done that which is evil in your sight; that you may be proved right when you speak, and justified when you judge.UGBehold, I was brought forth in iniquity. In sin my mother conceived me.UVBehold, you desire truth in the inward parts. You teach me wisdom in the inmost place.UTPurify me with hyssop, and I will be clean. Wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.UOLet me hear joy and gladness, That the bones which you have broken may rejoice.U?Hide your face from my sins, and blot out all of my iniquities.UBCreate in me a clean heart, O God. Renew a right spirit within me.UKDon't throw me from your presence, and don't take your holy Spirit from me.UIRestore to me the joy of your salvation. Uphold me with a willing spirit.UMThen I will teach transgressors your ways. Sinners shall be converted to you.UrDeliver me from bloodguiltiness, O God, the God of my salvation. My tongue shall sing aloud of your righteousness.U7Lord, open my lips. My mouth shall declare your praise.UdFor you don't delight in sacrifice, or else I would give it. You have no pleasure in burnt offering.UdThe sacrifices of God are a broken spirit. A broken and contrite heart, O God, you will not despise.UDDo well in your good pleasure to Zion. Build the walls of Jerusalem.UîThen you will delight in the sacrifices of righteousness, in burnt offerings and in whole burnt offerings. Then they will offer bulls on your altar.t(UÑ[For the Chief Musician. A contemplation by David, when Doeg the Edomite came and told Saul, "David has come to Abimelech's house."]UTWhy do you boast of mischief, mighty man? God's loving kindness endures continually.UGYour tongue plots destruction, like a sharp razor, working deceitfully.UJYou love evil more than good, lying rather than speaking the truth. Selah.U3You love all devouring words, you deceitful tongue.UéGod will likewise destroy you forever. He will take you up, and pluck you out of your tent, and root you out of the land of the living. Selah.UCThe righteous also will see it, and fear, and laugh at him, saying,Uì"Behold, this is the man who didn't make God his strength, but trusted in the abundance of his riches, and strengthened himself in his wickedness."UnBut as for me, I am like a green olive tree in God's house. I trust in God's loving kindness forever and ever.UÉI will give you