ion of the wicked. For they bring suffering on me. In anger they hold a grudge against me.UNMy heart is severely pained within me. The terrors of death have fallen on me.UEFearfulness and trembling have come on me. Horror has overwhelmed me.UPI said, "Oh that I had wings like a dove! Then I would fly away, and be at rest.UMBehold, then I would wander far off. I would lodge in the wilderness." Selah.U<"I would hurry to a shelter from the stormy wind and storm."UaConfuse them, Lord, and confound their language, for I have seen violence and strife in the city.USDay and night they prowl around on its walls. Malice and abuse are also within her.URDestructive forces are within her. Threats and lies don't depart from her streets.UÆFor it was not an enemy who insulted me, then I could have endured it. Neither was it he who hated me who raised himself up against me, then I would have hid myself from him.UDBut it was you, a man like me, my companion, and my familiar friend.UIWe took sweet fellowship together. We walked in God's house with company.U~Let death come suddenly on them. Let them go down alive into Sheol. For wickedness is in their dwelling, in the midst of them.U3As for me, I will call on God. Yahweh will save me.UQEvening, morning, and at noon, I will cry out in distress. He will hear my voice.UlHe has redeemed my soul in peace from the battle that was against me, although there are many who oppose me.UiGod, who is enthroned forever, will hear, and answer them. Selah.  They never change, who don't fear God.UFHe raises his hands against his friends. He has violated his covenant.UrHis mouth was smooth as butter, but his heart was war. His words were softer than oil, yet they were drawn swords.UcCast your burden on Yahweh, and he will sustain you. He will never allow the righteous to be moved.UõBut you, God, will bring them down into the pit of destruction. Bloodthirsty and deceitful men shall not live out half their days, but I will trust in you.t(UÇ[For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Silent Dove in Distant Lands." A poem by David, when the Philistines seized him in Gath.]UbBe merciful to me, God, for man wants to swallow me up. All day long, he attacks and oppresses me.U^My enemies want to swallow me up all day long, for they are many who fight proudly against me.U-When I am afraid, I will put my trust in you.UaIn God, I praise his word. In God, I put my trust. I will not be afraid. What can flesh do to me?UMAll day long they twist my words. All their thoughts are against me for evil.UJThey conspire and lurk, watching my steps, they are eager to take my life.UCShall they escape by iniquity? In anger cast down the peoples, God.UVYou number my wanderings. You put my tears into your bottle. Aren't they in your book?UXThen my enemies shall turn back in the day that I call. I know this, that God is for me.UBIn God, I will praise his word. In Yahweh, I will praise his word.UHI have put my trust in God. I will not be afraid. What can man do to me?U=Your vows are on me, God. I will give thank offerings to you.UÖFor you have delivered my soul from death, and prevented my feet from falling, that I may walk before God in the light of the living.t(Up[For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Do Not Destroy." A poem by David, when he fled from Saul, in the cave.]UúBe merciful to me, God, be merciful to me, for my soul takes refuge in you. Yes, in the shadow of your wings, I will take refuge, until disaster has passed.UGI cry out to God Most High, to God who accomplishes my requests for me.UâHe will send from heaven, and save me, he rebukes the one who is pursuing me. Selah. God will send out his loving kindness and his truth.UóMy soul is among lions. I lie among those who are set on fire, even the sons of men, whose teeth are spears and arrows, and their tongue a sharp sword.UJBe exalted, God, above the heavens! Let your glory be above all the earth!UÉThey have prepared a net for my steps. My soul is bowed down. They dig a pit before me. They fall into its midst themselves. Selah.UYMy heart is steadfast, God, my heart is steadfast. I will sing, yes, I will sing praises.UGWake up, my glory! Wake up, psaltery and harp! I will wake up the dawn.UaI will give thanks to you, Lord, among the peoples. I will sing praises to you among the nations.USFor your great loving kindness reaches to the heavens, and your truth to the skies.UIBe exalted, God, above the heavens. Let your glory be over all the earth.t(UK[For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Do Not Destroy." A poem by David.]UZDo you indeed speak righteousness, silent ones? Do you judge blamelessly, you sons of men?U^No, in your heart you plot injustice. You measure out the violence of your hands in the earth.U]The wicked go astray from the womb. They are wayward as soon as they are born, speaking lies.UQTheir poison is like the poison of a snake; like a deaf cobra that stops its ear,UYwhich doesn't listen to the voice of charmers, no matter how skillful the charmer may be.U]Break their teeth, God, in their mouth. Break out the great teeth of the young lions, Yahweh.UaLet them vanish as water that flows away. When they draw the bow, let their arrows be made blunt.UiLet them be like a snail which melts and passes away, like the stillborn child, who has not seen the sun.UeBefore your pots can feel the heat of the thorns, he will sweep away the green and the burning alike.UjThe righteous shall rejoice when he sees the vengeance. He shall wash his feet in the blood of the wicked;UÄso that men shall say, "Most certainly there is a reward for the righteous. Most certainly there is a God who judges the earth."t(UÉ[For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Do Not Destroy." A poem by David, when Saul sent, and they watched the house to kill him.]UUDeliver me from my enemies, my God. Set me on high from those who rise up against me.UKDeliver me from the workers of iniquity. Save me from the bloodthirsty men.UçFor, behold, they lie in wait for my soul. The mighty gather themselves together against me, not for my disobedience, nor for my sin, Yahweh.UTI have done no wrong, yet they are ready to attack me. Rise up, behold, and help me!UÄYou, Yahweh God of Armies, the God of Israel, rouse yourself to punish the nations. Show no mercy to the wicked traitors. Selah.UEThey return at evening, howling like dogs, and prowl around the city.U^Behold, they spew with their mouth. Swords are in their lips, "For," they say, "who hears us?"U=But you, Yahweh, laugh at them. You scoff at all the nations.U;Oh, my Strength, I watch for you, for God is my high tower.UaMy God will go before me with his loving kindness. God will let me look at my enemies in triumph.UkDon't kill them, or my people may forget. Scatter them by your power, and bring them down, Lord our shield.UÖFor the sin of their mouth, and the words of their lips, let them be caught in their pride, for the curses and lies which they utter.UÜConsume them in wrath. Consume them, and they will be no more. Let them know that God rules in Jacob, to the ends of the earth. Selah.UMAt evening let them return. Let them howl like a dog, and go around the city.UTThey shall wander up and down for food, and wait all night if they aren't satisfied.U•But I will sing of your strength. Yes, I will sing aloud of your loving kindness in the morning. For you have been my high tower, a refuge in the day of my distress.UXTo you, my strength, I will sing praises. For God is my high tower, the God of my mercy.t(U‚[For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "The Lily of the Covenant." A teaching poem by David, when he fought with Aram Naharaim and with Aram Zobah, and Joab returned, and killed twelve thousand of Edom in the Valley of Salt.]U[God, you have rejected us. You have broken us down. You have been angry. Restore us, again.UTYou have made the land tremble. You have torn it. Mend its fractures, for it quakes.U^You have shown your people hard things. You have made us drink the wine that makes us stagger.UdYou have given a banner to those who fear you, that it may be displayed because of the truth. Selah.UPSo that your beloved may be delivered, save with your right hand, and answer us.UqGod has spoken from his sanctuary: "I will triumph. I will divide Shechem, and measure out the valley of Succoth.UbGilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine. Ephraim also is the defense of my head. Judah is my scepter.UXMoab is my wash basin. I will throw my shoe on Edom. I shout in triumph over Philistia."U?Who will bring me into the strong city? Who has led me to Edom?UEHaven't you, God, rejected us? You don't go out with our armies, God.U@Give us help against the adversary, for the help of man is vain.UTThrough God we shall do valiantly, for it is he who will tread down our adversaries.t(U>[For the Chief Musician. For a stringed instrument. By David.]U&Hear my cry, God. Listen to my prayer.UwFrom the end of the earth, I will call to you, when my heart is overwhelmed. Lead me to the rock that is higher than I.UAFor you have been a refuge for me, a strong tower from the enemy.UZI will dwell in your tent forever. I will take refuge in the shelter of your wings. Selah.U]For you, God, have heard my vows. You have given me the heritage of those who fear your name.UEYou will prolong the king's life; his years shall be for generations.UtHe shall be enthroned in God's presence forever. Appoint your loving kindness and truth, that they may preserve him.UMSo I will sing praise to your name forever, that I may fulfill my vows daily.t(U8[For the Chief Musician. To Jeduthan. A Psalm by David.]U5My soul rests in God alone. My salvation is from him.USHe alone is my rock and my salvation, my fortress-- I will never be greatly shaken.UnHow long will you assault a man, would all of you throw him down, Like a leaning wall, like a tottering fence?UåThey fully intend to throw him down from his lofty place. They delight in lies. They bless with their mouth, but they curse inwardly. Selah.UGMy soul, wait in