s.UvYou are awesome, God, in your sanctuaries. The God of Israel gives strength and power to his people. Praise be to God!t(U<[For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Lilies." By David.]U5Save me, God, for the waters have come up to my neck!UlI sink in deep mire, where there is no foothold. I have come into deep waters, where the floods overflow me.UNI am weary with my crying. My throat is dry. My eyes fail, looking for my God.U∑Those who hate me without a cause are more than the hairs of my head. Those who want to cut me off, being my enemies wrongfully, are mighty. I have to restore what I didn't take away.U=God, you know my foolishness. My sins aren't hidden from you.UúDon't let those who wait for you be shamed through me, Lord Yahweh of Armies. Don't let those who seek you be brought to dishonor through me, God of Israel.UHBecause for your sake, I have borne reproach. Shame has covered my face.UJI have become a stranger to my brothers, an alien to my mother's children.UcFor the zeal of your house consumes me. The reproaches of those who reproach you have fallen on me.U2When I wept and I fasted, that was to my reproach.U=When I made sackcloth my clothing, I became a byword to them.UHThose who sit in the gate talk about me. I am the song of the drunkards.UõBut as for me, my prayer is to you, Yahweh, in an acceptable time. God, in the abundance of your loving kindness, answer me in the truth of your salvation.UzDeliver me out of the mire, and don't let me sink. Let me be delivered from those who hate me, and out of the deep waters.UtDon't let the flood waters overwhelm me, neither let the deep swallow me up. Don't let the pit shut its mouth on me.UsAnswer me, Yahweh, for your loving kindness is good. According to the multitude of your tender mercies, turn to me.UQDon't hide your face from your servant, for I am in distress. Answer me speedily!UEDraw near to my soul, and redeem it. Ransom me because of my enemies.USYou know my reproach, my shame, and my dishonor. My