raises to you with the lyre, Holy One of Israel.UTMy lips shall shout for joy! My soul, which you have redeemed, sings praises to you!UàMy tongue will also talk about your righteousness all day long, for they are disappointed, and they are confounded, who want to harm me.t(U[By Solomon.]UEGod, give the king your justice; your righteousness to the royal son.UIHe will judge your people with righteousness, and your poor with justice.U_The mountains shall bring prosperity to the people. The hills bring the fruit of righteousness.UuHe will judge the poor of the people. He will save the children of the needy, and will break the oppressor in pieces.U_They shall fear you while the sun endures; and as long as the moon, throughout all generations.UOHe will come down like rain on the mown grass, as showers that water the earth.U]In his days, the righteous shall flourish, and abundance of peace, until the moon is no more.UUHe shall have dominion also from sea to sea, from the River to the ends of the earth.UXThose who dwell in the wilderness shall bow before him. His enemies shall lick the dust.UkThe kings of Tarshish and of the islands will bring tribute. The kings of Sheba and Seba shall offer gifts.UGYes, all kings shall fall down before him. All nations shall serve him.UIFor he will deliver the needy when he cries; the poor, who has no helper.UMHe will have pity on the poor and needy. He will save the souls of the needy.UbHe will redeem their soul from oppression and violence. Their blood will be precious in his sight.UáThey shall live, and to him shall be given of the gold of Sheba. Men shall pray for him continually. They shall bless him all day long.UãThere shall be abundance of grain throughout the land. Its fruit sways like Lebanon. Let it flourish, thriving like the grass of the field.UÄHis name endures forever. His name continues as long as the sun. Men shall be blessed by him. All nations will call him blessed.UKPraise be to Yahweh God, the God of Israel, who alone