aven? There is no one on earth who I desire besides you.UXMy flesh and my heart fails, but God is the strength of my heart and my portion forever.UmFor, behold, those who are far from you shall perish. You have destroyed all those who are unfaithful to you.UuBut it is good for me to come close to God. I have made the Lord Yahweh my refuge, that I may tell of all your works.t(U[A contemplation by Asaph.]UeGod, why have you rejected us forever? Why does your anger smolder against the sheep of your pasture?UôRemember your congregation, which you purchased of old, which you have redeemed to be the tribe of your inheritance; Mount Zion, in which you have lived.U`Lift up your feet to the perpetual ruins, all the evil that the enemy has done in the sanctuary.UfYour adversaries have roared in the midst of your assembly. They have set up their standards as signs.UHThey behaved like men wielding axes, cutting through a thicket of trees.UANow they break all its carved work down with hatchet and hammers.UbThey have burned your sanctuary to the ground. They have profaned the dwelling place of your Name.UÇThey said in their heart, "We will crush them completely." They have burned up all the places in the land where God was worshiped.UpWe see no miraculous signs. There is no longer any prophet, neither is there among us anyone who knows how long.UYHow long, God, shall the adversary reproach? Shall the enemy blaspheme your name forever?UbWhy do you draw back your hand, even your right hand? Take it out of your pocket and consume them!UGYet God is my King of old, working salvation in the midst of the earth.U\You divided the sea by your strength. You broke the heads of the sea monsters in the waters.U`You broke the heads of Leviathan in pieces. You gave him as food to people and desert creatures.U<You opened up spring and stream. You dried up mighty rivers.USThe day is yours, the night is also yours. You have prepared the light and the sun.UNYou have set all the boundaries of the ea