ed out.UÖLet the sighing of the prisoner come before you. According to the greatness of your power, preserve those who are sentenced to death.UpPay back to our neighbors seven times into their bosom their reproach with which they have reproached you, Lord.U{So we, your people and sheep of your pasture, will give you thanks forever. We will praise you forever, to all generations.t(UX[For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "The Lilies of the Covenant." A Psalm by Asaph.]UkHear us, Shepherd of Israel, you who lead Joseph like a flock, you who sit above the cherubim, shine forth.UNBefore Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh, stir up your might! Come to save us!UCTurn us again, God. Cause your face to shine, and we will be saved.USYahweh God of Armies, How long will you be angry against the prayer of your people?UZYou have fed them with the bread of tears, and given them tears to drink in large measure.UXYou make us a source of contention to our neighbors. Our enemies laugh among themselves.UMTurn us again, God of Armies. Cause your face to shine, and we will be saved.UKYou brought a vine out of Egypt. You drove out the nations, and planted it.UFYou cleared the ground for it. It took deep root, and filled the land.UNThe mountains were covered with its shadow. Its boughs were like God's cedars.U=It sent out its branches to the sea, Its shoots to the River.USWhy have you broken down its walls, so that all those who pass by the way pluck it?UNThe boar out of the wood ravages it. The wild animals of the field feed on it.U[Turn again, we beg you, God of Armies. Look down from heaven, and see, and visit this vine,UVthe stock which your right hand planted, the branch that you made strong for yourself.UAIt's burned with fire. It's cut down. They perish at your rebuke.UdLet your hand be on the man of your right hand, on the son of man whom you made strong for yourself.ULSo we will not turn away from you. Revive us, and we will call on your name.UTTurn us again, Yahweh God of Armies. Cause your face to shine, and we will be saved.t(U=[For the Chief Musician. On an instrument of Gath. By Asaph.]UISing aloud to God, our strength! Make a joyful shout to the God of Jacob!UMRaise a song, and bring here the tambourine, the pleasant lyre with the harp.UEBlow the trumpet at the New Moon, at the full moon, on our feast day.UAFor it is a statute for Israel, an ordinance of the God of Jacob.UzHe appointed it in Joseph for a testimony, when he went out over the land of Egypt, I heard a language that I didn't know.UN"I removed his shoulder from the burden. His hands were freed from the basket.UâYou called in trouble, and I delivered you. I answered you in the secret place of thunder. I tested you at the waters of Meribah." Selah.UO"Hear, my people, and I will testify to you, Israel, if you would listen to me!UPThere shall be no strange god in you, neither shall you worship any foreign god.UmI am Yahweh, your God, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt. Open your mouth wide, and I will fill it.UCBut my people didn't listen to my voice. Israel desired none of me.UdSo I let them go after the stubbornness of their hearts, that they might walk in their own counsels.UHOh that my people would listen to me, that Israel would walk in my ways!UNI would soon subdue their enemies, and turn my hand against their adversaries.UVThe haters of Yahweh would cringe before him, and their punishment would last forever.UmBut he would have also fed them with the finest of the wheat. I will satisfy you with honey out of the rock."t(U[A Psalm by Asaph.]U=God presides in the great assembly. He judges among the gods.UM"How long will you judge unjustly, and show partiality to the wicked?" Selah.U^"Defend the weak, the poor, and the fatherless. Maintain the rights of the poor and oppressed.UGRescue the weak and needy. Deliver them out of the hand of the wicked."UThey don't know, neither do they understand. They walk back and forth in darkness. All the foundations of the earth ar