e way for his steps.t(U[A Prayer by David.]U5Hear, Yahweh, and answer me, for I am poor and needy.USPreserve my soul, for I am godly. You, my God, save your servant who trusts in you.U8Be merciful to me, Lord, for I call to you all day long.UNBring joy to the soul of your servant, for to you, Lord, do I lift up my soul.UhFor you, Lord, are good, and ready to forgive; abundant in loving kindness to all those who call on you.U=Hear, Yahweh, my prayer. Listen to the voice of my petitions.UDIn the day of my trouble I will call on you, for you will answer me.UMThere is no one like you among the gods, Lord, nor any deeds like your deeds.U_All nations you have made will come and worship before you, Lord. They shall glorify your name.U=For you are great, and do wondrous things. You are God alone.U`Teach me your way, Yahweh. I will walk in your truth. Make my heart undivided to fear your name.UZI will praise you, Lord my God, with my whole heart. I will glorify your name forevermore.U^For your loving kindness is great toward me. You have delivered my soul from the lowest Sheol.UåGod, the proud have risen up against me. A company of violent men have sought after my soul, and they don't hold regard for you before them.UiBut you, Lord, are a merciful and gracious God, slow to anger, and abundant in loving kindness and truth.UdTurn to me, and have mercy on me! Give your strength to your servant. Save the son of your handmaid.UâShow me a sign of your goodness, that those who hate me may see it, and be shamed, because you, Yahweh, have helped me, and comforted me.t(U'[A Psalm by the sons of Korah; a Song.]U(His foundation is in the holy mountains.UDYahweh loves the gates of Zion more than all the dwellings of Jacob.U9Glorious things are spoken about you, city of God. Selah.UÜI will record Rahab and Babylon among those who acknowledge me. Behold, Philistia, Tyre, and also Ethiopia: "This one was born there."UpYes, of Zion it will be said, "This one and that one was born in her;" t