e evil, and choose the good, the land whose two kings you abhor shall be forsaken.UßYahweh will bring on you, on your people, and on your father's house, days that have not come, from the day that Ephraim departed from Judah; even the king of Assyria.U•It will happen in that day that Yahweh will whistle for the fly that is in the uttermost part of the rivers of Egypt, and for the bee that is in the land of Assyria.UÇThey shall come, and shall all rest in the desolate valleys, in the clefts of the rocks, on all thorn hedges, and on all pastures.U¿In that day the Lord will shave with a razor that is hired in the parts beyond the River, even with the king of Assyria, the head and the hair of the feet; and it shall also consume the beard.USIt shall happen in that day that a man shall keep alive a young cow, and two sheep;U≥and it shall happen, that because of the abundance of milk which they shall give he shall eat butter: for everyone will eat butter and honey that is left in the midst of the land.UãIt will happen in that day that every place where there were a thousand vines at a thousand silver shekels, shall be for briers and thorns.U^People will go there with arrows and with bow, because all the land will be briers and thorns.U∑All the hills that were cultivated with the hoe, you shall not come there for fear of briers and thorns; but it shall be for the sending forth of oxen, and for the treading of sheep."t(NUgYahweh said to me, "Take a large tablet, and write on it with a man's pen, 'For Maher Shalal Hash Baz;'Urand I will take for myself faithful witnesses to testify: Uriah the priest, and Zechariah the son of Jeberechiah."U|I went to the prophetess, and she conceived, and bore a son. Then said Yahweh to me, "Call his name 'Maher Shalal Hash Baz.'U£For before the child knows how to say, 'My father,' and, 'My mother,' the riches of Damascus and the spoil of Samaria will be carried away by the king of Assyria."U%Yahweh spoke to me yet again, saying,Up"Because this people have refused the waters of Shiloah that go softly, and rejoice in Rezin and Remaliah's son;Uønow therefore, behold, the Lord brings upon them the mighty flood waters of the River: the king of Assyria and all his glory. It will come up over all its channels, and go over all its banks.UµIt will sweep onward into Judah. It will overflow and pass through; it will reach even to the neck; and the stretching out of its wings will fill the breadth of your land, Immanuel.U°Make an uproar, you peoples, and be broken in pieces! Listen, all you from far countries: dress for battle, and be shattered! Dress for battle, and be shattered!UuTake counsel together, and it will be brought to nothing; speak the word, and it will not stand: for God is with us."UpFor Yahweh spoke thus to me with a strong hand, and instructed me not to walk in the way of this people, saying,UÜ"Don't say, 'A conspiracy!' concerning all about which this people say, 'A conspiracy!' neither fear their threats, nor be terrorized.UkYahweh of Armies is who you must regard as holy. He is the one you must fear. He is the one you must dread.UvHe will be a sanctuary, but for both houses of Israel, he will be a trap and a snare for the inhabitants of Jerusalem.UHMany will stumble over it, fall, be broken, be snared, and be captured."U7Wrap up the testimony. Seal the law among my disciples.U\I will wait for Yahweh, who hides his face from the house of Jacob, and I will look for him.UåBehold, I and the children whom Yahweh has given me are for signs and for wonders in Israel from Yahweh of Armies, who dwells in Mount Zion.U”When they tell you, "Consult with those who have familiar spirits and with the wizards, who chirp and who mutter:" shouldn't a people consult with their God? Should they consult the dead on behalf of the living?UvTurn to the law and to the testimony! If they don't speak according to this word, surely there is no morning for them.U¬They will pass through it, sore distressed and hungry; and it will happen that when they are hungry, they will worry, and curse by their king and by their God. They will turn their faces upward,Uuand look to the earth, and see distress, darkness, and the gloom of anguish. They will be driven into thick darkness.t(NT	␀␀But there shall be no more gloom for her who was in anguish. In the former time, he brought into contempt the land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtali; but in the latter time he has made it glorious, by the way of the sea, beyond the Jordan, Galilee of the nations.UåThe people who walked in darkness have seen a great light. Those who lived in the land of the shadow of death, on them the light has shined.U°You have multiplied the nation. You have increased their joy. They rejoice before you according to the joy in harvest, as men rejoice when they divide the spoil.U}For the yoke of his burden, and the staff of his shoulder, the rod of his oppressor, you have broken as in the day of Midian.UÅFor all the armor of the armed man in the noisy battle, and the garments rolled in blood, will be for burning, fuel for the fire.UºFor to us a child is born. To us a son is given; and the government will be on his shoulders. His name will be called Wonderful, Counselor, Mighty God, Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.T␀␀Of the increase of his government and of peace there shall be no end, on the throne of David, and on his kingdom, to establish it, and to uphold it with justice and with righteousness from that time on, even forever. The zeal of Yahweh of Armies will perform this.U8The Lord sent a word into Jacob, and it falls on Israel.UwAll the people will know, including Ephraim and the inhabitants of Samaria, who say in pride and in arrogance of heart,Uç"The bricks have fallen, but we will build with cut stone. The sycamore fig trees have been cut down, but we will put cedars in their place."UhTherefore Yahweh will set up on high against him the adversaries of Rezin, and will stir up his enemies,UØThe Syrians in front, a