t still.UNAlas Assyrian, the rod of my anger, the staff in whose hand is my indignation!UƒI will send him against a profane nation, and against the people who anger me will I give him a command to take the spoil and to take the prey, and to tread them down like the mire of the streets.UÅHowever he doesn't mean so, neither does his heart think so; but it is in his heart to destroy, and to cut off not a few nations.U-For he says, "Aren't all of my princes kings?USIsn't Calno like Carchemish? Isn't Hamath like Arpad? Isn't Samaria like Damascus?"UqAs my hand has found the kingdoms of the idols, whose engraved images exceeded those of Jerusalem and of Samaria;UWshall I not, as I have done to Samaria and her idols, so do to Jerusalem and her idols?U‹Therefore it will happen that, when the Lord has performed his whole work on Mount Zion and on Jerusalem, I will punish the fruit of the willful proud heart of the king of Assyria, and the insolence of his haughty looks.UFor he has said, "By the strength of my hand I have done it, and by my wisdom; for I have understanding: and I have removed the boundaries of the peoples, and have robbed their treasures. Like a valiant man I have brought down their rulers.U’My hand has found the riches of the peoples like a nest, and like one gathers eggs that are abandoned, have I gathered all the earth. There was no one who moved their wing, or that opened their mouth, or chirped."UŒShould an axe brag against him who chops with it? Should a saw exalt itself above him who saws with it? As if a rod should lift those who lift it up, or as if a staff should lift up someone who is not wood.UîTherefore the Lord, Yahweh of Armies, will send among his fat ones leanness; and under his glory a burning will be kindled like the burning of fire.UáThe light of Israel will be for a fire, and his Holy One for a flame; and it will burn and devour his thorns and his briers in one day.UÑHe will consume the glory of his forest, and of his fruitful field, bot