ihor, the harvest of the Nile, was her revenue. She was the market of nations.U¥Be ashamed, Sidon; for the sea has spoken, the stronghold of the sea, saying, "I have not travailed, nor brought forth, neither have I nourished young men, nor brought up virgins."UNWhen the report comes to Egypt, they will be in anguish at the report of Tyre.U:Pass over to Tarshish! Wail, you inhabitants of the coast!UhIs this your joyous city, whose antiquity is of ancient days, whose feet carried her far away to travel?UÜWho has planned this against Tyre, the giver of crowns, whose merchants are princes, whose traffickers are the honorable of the earth?UxYahweh of Armies has planned it, to stain the pride of all glory, to bring into contempt all the honorable of the earth.U[Pass through your land like the Nile, daughter of Tarshish. There is no restraint any more.UÉHe has stretched out his hand over the sea. He has shaken the kingdoms. Yahweh has ordered the destruction of Canaan's strongholds.UãHe said, "You shall rejoice no more, you oppressed virgin daughter of Sidon. Arise, pass over to Kittim. Even there you will have no rest."U¬Behold, the land of the Chaldeans. This people was not. The Assyrians founded it for those who dwell in the wilderness. They set up their towers. They overthrew its palaces. They made it a ruin.U?Howl, you ships of Tarshish, for your stronghold is laid waste!UƒIt will come to pass in that day that Tyre will be forgotten seventy years, according to the days of one king. After the end of seventy years it will be to Tyre like in the song of the prostitute.UáTake a harp; go about the city, you prostitute that has been forgotten. Make sweet melody. Sing many songs, that you may be remembered.U It will happen after the end of seventy years that Yahweh will visit Tyre, and she shall return to her wages, and will play the prostitute with all the kingdoms of the world on the surface of the earth.UÕHer merchandise and her wages will be holiness to Yahweh. It will not be treasured nor laid up; for her merchandise will be for those who dwell before Yahweh, to eat sufficiently, and for durable clothing.t(NUiBehold, Yahweh makes the earth empty, makes it waste, turns it upside down, and scatters its inhabitants.T␀␀It will be as with the people, so with the priest; as with the servant, so with his master; as with the maid, so with her mistress; as with the buyer, so with the seller; as with the creditor, so with the debtor; as with the taker of interest, so with the giver of interest.UZThe earth will be utterly emptied and utterly laid waste; for Yahweh has spoken this word.UmThe earth mourns and fades away. The world languishes and fades away. The lofty people of the earth languish.UñThe earth also is polluted under its inhabitants, because they have transgressed the laws, violated the statutes, and broken the everlasting covenant.UûTherefore the curse has devoured the earth, and those who dwell therein are found guilty. Therefore the inhabitants of the earth are burned, and few men left.UEThe new wine mourns. The vine languishes. All the merry-hearted sigh.UaThe mirth of tambourines ceases. The sound of those who rejoice ends. The joy of the harp ceases.UXThey will not drink wine with a song. Strong drink will be bitter to those who drink it.URThe confused city is broken down. Every house is shut up, that no man may come in.UiThere is a crying in the streets because of the wine. All joy is darkened. The mirth of the land is gone.UHThe city is left in desolation, and the gate is struck with destruction.UäFor it will be so in the midst of the earth among the peoples, as the shaking of an olive tree, as the gleanings when the vintage is done.UhThese shall lift up their voice. They will shout for the majesty of Yahweh. They cry aloud from the sea.UlTherefore glorify Yahweh in the east, even the name of Yahweh, the God of Israel, in the islands of the sea!U‚From the uttermost part of the earth have we heard songs. Glory to the righteous! But I said, "I pine away! I pine away! woe is me!" The treacherous have dealt treacherously. Yes, the treacherous have dealt very treacherously.UBFear, the pit, and the snare, are on you who inhabitant the earth.UÌIt will happen that he who flees from the noise of the fear will fall into the pit; and he who comes up out of the midst of the pit will be taken in the snare; for the windows on high are opened, and the foundations of the earth tremble.UTThe earth is utterly broken. The earth is torn apart. The earth is shaken violently.U¢The earth will stagger like a drunken man, and will sway back and forth like a hammock. Its disobedience will be heavy on it, and it will fall and not rise again.UIt shall happen in that day that Yahweh will punish the army of the high ones on high, and the kings of the earth on the earth.UïThey shall be gathered together, as prisoners are gathered in the pit, and shall be shut up in the prison; and after many days shall they be visited.UùThen the moon shall be confounded, and the sun ashamed; for Yahweh of Armies will reign on Mount Zion, and in Jerusalem; and before his elders will be glory.t(NU£Yahweh, you are my God. I will exalt you! I will praise your name, for you have done wonderful things, things planned long ago, in complete faithfulness and truth.UÄFor you have made a city into a heap, a fortified city into a ruin, a palace of strangers to be no city. It will never be built.UTTherefore a strong people will glorify you. A city of awesome nations will fear you.UÀFor you have been a stronghold to the poor, a stronghold to the needy in his distress, a refuge from the storm, a shade from the heat, when the blast of the dreaded ones is like a storm against the wall.UùAs the heat in a dry place will you bring down the noise of strangers; as the heat by the shade of a cloud, the song of the dreaded ones will be brought low.U§In this mountain, Yahweh of Armies will make all peoples a feast of fat things, a feast of choice wines, of fat things full of marrow, of well refined choice wines.UÉHe will destroy in this mountain the surface of the covering that covers all peoples, and the veil that is spread over all nations.U∫He has swallowed up death forever! The Lord Yahweh will wipe away tears from off all faces. He will take the reproach of his people away from off all the earth, for Yahweh has spoken it.UªIt shall be said in that day, "Behold, this is our God! We have waited for him, and he will save us! This is Yahweh! We have waited for him. We will be glad and rejoice in his salvation!"UòFor in this mountain the hand of Yahweh will rest. Moab will be trodden down in his place, even like straw is trodden down in the water of the dunghill.UúHe will spread out his hands in its midst, like one who swims spreads out hands to swim, but his pride will be humbled together with the craft of his hands.UkHe has brought the high fortress of your walls down, laid low, and brought to the ground, even to the dust.t(NUÄIn that day, this song will be sung in the land of Judah: "We have a strong city. God appoints salvation for walls and bulwarks.UOOpen the gates, that the righteous nation may enter: the one which keeps faith.UUYou will keep whoever's mind is steadfast in perfect peace, because he trusts in you.UDTrust in Yahweh forever; for in Yah, Yahweh, is an everlasting Rock.UíFor he has brought down those who dwell on high, the lofty city. He lays it low. He lays it low even to the ground. He brings it even to the dust.UUThe foot shall tread it down; Even the feet of the poor, and the steps of the needy."U]The way of the just is uprightness. You who are upright make the path of the righteous level.UxYes, in the way of your judgments, Yahweh, have we waited for you. Your name and your renown are the desire of our soul.U¬With my soul have I desired you in the night. Yes, with my spirit within me will I seek you earnestly; for when your judgments are in the earth, the inhabitants of the world learn righteousness.UùLet favor be shown to the wicked, yet he will not learn righteousness. In the land of uprightness he will deal wrongfully, and will not see Yahweh's majesty.UùYahweh, your hand is lifted up, yet they don't see; but they will see your zeal for the people, and be disappointed. Yes, fire will consume your adversaries.UTYahweh, you will ordain peace for us, for you have also worked all our works for us.UuYahweh our God, other lords besides you have had dominion over us, but by you only will we make mention of your name.UçThe dead shall not live. The deceased shall not rise. Therefore have you visited and destroyed them, and caused all memory of them to perish.UâYou have increased the nation, O Yahweh. You have increased the nation! You are glorified! You have enlarged all the borders of the land.UdYahweh, in trouble they have visited you. They poured out a prayer when your chastening was on them.UèLike as a woman with child, who draws near the time of her delivery, is in pain and cries out in her pangs; so we have been before you, Yahweh.U∏We have been with child. We have been in pain. We gave birth, it seems, only to wind. We have not worked any deliverance in the earth; neither have the inhabitants of the world fallen.U´Your dead shall live. My dead bodies shall arise. Awake and sing, you who dwell in the dust; for your dew is like the dew of herbs, and the earth will cast forth the dead.UåCome, my people, enter into your chambers, and shut your doors behind you. Hide yourself for a little moment, until the indignation is past.U∑For, behold, Yahweh comes forth out of his place to punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity. The earth also will disclose her blood, and will no longer cover her slain.t(NUªIn that day, Yahweh with his hard and great and strong sword will punish leviathan, the fleeing serpent, and leviathan the twisted serpent; and he will kill the dragon that is in the sea.U/In that day, sing to her, "A pleasant vineyard!UlI, Yahweh, am its keeper. I will water it every moment. Lest anyone damage it, I will keep it night and day.UÑWrath is not in me, but if I should find briers and thorns, I would do battle! I would march on them and I would burn them together.UfOr else let him take hold of my strength, that he may make peace with me. Let him make peace with me."UwIn days to come, Jacob will take root. Israel will blossom and bud. They will fill the surface of the world with fruit.UqHas he struck them as he struck those who struck them? Or are they killed like those who killed them were killed?UÅIn measure, when you send them away, you contend with them. He has removed them with his rough blast in the day of the east wind.T␀␀␀Therefore, by this the iniquity of Jacob will be forgiven, and this is all the fruit of taking away his sin: that he makes all the stones of the altar as chalk stones that are beaten in pieces, so that the Asherim and the incense altars shall rise no more.U¨For the fortified city is solitary, a habitation deserted and forsaken, like the wilderness. The calf will feed there, and there he will lie down, and consume its branches.U¯When its boughs are withered, they will be broken off. The women will come and set them on fire, for they are a people of no understanding. Therefore he who made them will not have compassion on them, and he who formed them will show them no favor.U¨It will happen in that day, that Yahweh will thresh from the flowing stream of the Euphrates to the brook of Egypt; and you will be gathered one by one, children of Israel.U˜It will happen in that day that a great trumpet will be blown; and those who were ready to perish in the land of Assyria, and those who were outcasts in the land of Egypt, shall come; and they will worship Yahweh in the holy mountain at Jerusalem.t(NU∑Woe to the crown of pride of the drunkards of Ephraim, and to the fading flower of his glorious beauty, which is on the head of the fertile valley of those who are overcome with wine