ved their heart far from me, and their fear of me is a commandment of men which has been taught;UŸtherefore, behold, I will proceed to do a marvelous work among this people, even a marvelous work and a wonder; and the wisdom of their wise men will perish, and the understanding of their prudent men will be hidden."UàWoe to those who deeply hide their counsel from Yahweh, and whose works are in the dark, and who say, "Who sees us?" and "Who knows us?"UﬁYou turn things upside down! Should the potter be thought to be like clay; that the thing made should say about him who made it, "He didn't make me;" or the thing formed say of him who formed it, "He has no understanding?"UàIsn't it yet a very little while, and Lebanon will be turned into a fruitful field, and the fruitful field will be regarded as a forest?UIn that day, the deaf will hear the words of the book, and the eyes of the blind will see out of obscurity and out of darkness.UqThe humble also will increase their joy in Yahweh, and the poor among men will rejoice in the Holy One of Israel.UtFor the ruthless is brought to nothing, and the scoffer ceases, and all those who are alert to do evil are cut off--Uówho cause a person to be indicted by a word, and lay a snare for the arbiter in the gate, and who deprive the innocent of justice with false testimony.UïTherefore thus says Yahweh, who redeemed Abraham, concerning the house of Jacob: "Jacob shall no longer be ashamed, neither shall his face grow pale.U¿But when he sees his children, the work of my hands, in the midst of him, they will sanctify my name. Yes, they will sanctify the Holy One of Jacob, and will stand in awe of the God of Israel.UhThey also who err in spirit will come to understanding, and those who grumble will receive instruction."t(NU¢"Woe to the rebellious children," says Yahweh, "who take counsel, but not from me; and who make an alliance, but not with my Spirit, that they may add sin to sin,U†who set out to go down into Egypt, and have not asked my advice; to strengthen themselves in the strength of Pharaoh, and to take refuge in the shadow of Egypt!UkTherefore the strength of Pharaoh will be your shame, and the refuge in the shadow of Egypt your confusion.UHFor their princes are at Zoan, and their ambassadors have come to Hanes.UàThey shall all be ashamed because of a people that can't profit them, that are not a help nor profit, but a shame, and also a reproach."T␀␀The burden of the animals of the South. Through the land of trouble and anguish, of the lioness and the lion, the viper and fiery flying serpent, they carry their riches on the shoulders of young donkeys, and their treasures on the humps of camels, to an unprofitable people.U]For Egypt helps in vain, and to no purpose; therefore have I called her Rahab who sits still.UzNow go, write it before them on a tablet, and inscribe it in a book, that it may be for the time to come forever and ever.U\For it is a rebellious people, lying children, children who will not hear the law of Yahweh;UÑwho tell the seers, "Don't see!" and to the prophets, "Don't prophesy to us right things. Tell us pleasant things. Prophesy deceits.UdGet out of the way. Turn aside from the path. Cause the Holy One of Israel to cease from before us."UÖTherefore thus says the Holy One of Israel, "Because you despise this word, and trust in oppression and perverseness, and rely on it;Uétherefore this iniquity shall be to you like a breach ready to fall, swelling out in a high wall, whose breaking comes suddenly in an instant.UÂHe will break it as a potter's vessel is broken, breaking it in pieces without sparing, so that there won't be found among the broken piece a piece good enough to take fire from the hearth, or to dip up water out of the cistern."U§For thus said the Lord Yahweh, the Holy One of Israel, "You will be saved in returning and rest. Your strength will be in quietness and in confidence." You refused,Uòbut you said, "No, for we will flee on horses;" therefore you 