st.UABeat your breasts for the pleasant fields, for the fruitful vine.UeThorns and briars will come up on my people's land; yes, on all the houses of joy in the joyous city.U´For the palace will be forsaken. The populous city will be deserted. The hill and the watchtower will be for dens forever, a delight for wild donkeys, a pasture of flocks;UäUntil the Spirit is poured on us from on high, and the wilderness becomes a fruitful field, and the fruitful field is considered a forest.U_Then justice will dwell in the wilderness; and righteousness will remain in the fruitful field.UkThe work of righteousness will be peace; and the effect of righteousness, quietness and confidence forever.U^My people will abide in a peaceful habitation, in safe dwellings, and in quiet resting places.UDThough hail flattens the forest, and the city is leveled completely.UZBlessed are you who sow beside all waters, who send out the feet of the ox and the donkey.t(NU÷Woe to you who destroy, but you weren't destroyed; and who betray, but nobody betrayed you! When you have finished destroying, you will be destroyed; and when you have made an end of betrayal, you will be betrayed.U|Yahweh, be gracious to us. We have waited for you. Be our strength every morning, our salvation also in the time of trouble.UiAt the noise of the thunder, the peoples have fled. When you lift yourself up, the nations are scattered.U\Your spoil will be gathered as the caterpillar gathers. Men will leap on it as locusts leap.U\Yahweh is exalted, for he dwells on high. He has filled Zion with justice and righteousness.UzThere will be stability in your times, abundance of salvation, wisdom, and knowledge. The fear of Yahweh is your treasure.UOBehold, their valiant ones cry outside; the ambassadors of peace weep bitterly.UThe highways are desolate. The traveling man ceases. The covenant is broken. He has despised the cities. He doesn't regard man.UâThe land mourns and languishes. Lebanon is confounded and withers away. Sh