r clothing, and your garments like him who treads in the wine vat?U‚I have trodden the winepress alone; and of the peoples there was no man with me: yes, I trod them in my anger, and trampled them in my wrath; and their lifeblood is sprinkled on my garments, and I have stained all my clothing.UNFor the day of vengeance was in my heart, and the year of my redeemed is come.UùI looked, and there was none to help; and I wondered that there was none to uphold: therefore my own arm brought salvation to me; and my wrath, it upheld me.UtI trod down the peoples in my anger, and made them drunk in my wrath, and I poured out their lifeblood on the earth.T)␀␀I will make mention of the loving kindnesses of Yahweh, [and] the praises of Yahweh, according to all that Yahweh has bestowed on us, and the great goodness toward the house of Israel, which he has bestowed on them according to his mercies, and according to the multitude of his loving kindnesses.UdFor he said, Surely, they are my people, children who will not deal falsely: so he was their Savior.UπIn all their affliction he was afflicted, and the angel of his presence saved them: in his love and in his pity he redeemed them; and he bore them, and carried them all the days of old.U}But they rebelled, and grieved his holy Spirit: therefore he was turned to be their enemy, [and] himself fought against them.UœThen he remembered the days of old, Moses [and] his people, [saying], Where is he who brought them up out of the sea with the shepherds of his flock? where is he who put his holy Spirit in the midst of them?UÜwho caused his glorious arm to go at the right hand of Moses? who divided the waters before them, to make himself an everlasting name?U[who led them through the depths, as a horse in the wilderness, so that they didn't stumble?UóAs the livestock that go down into the valley, the Spirit of Yahweh caused them to rest; so did you lead your people, to make yourself a glorious name.U»Look down from heaven, and see from the habitation of your holiness and of your glory: where are your zeal and your mighty acts? the yearning of your heart and your compassion is restrained toward me.U§For you are our Father, though Abraham doesn't know us, and Israel does not acknowledge us: you, Yahweh, are our Father; our Redeemer from everlasting is your name.UòO Yahweh, why do you make us to err from your ways, and harden our heart from your fear? Return for your servants' sake, the tribes of your inheritance.UeYour holy people possessed [it] but a little while: our adversaries have trodden down your sanctuary.U_We are become as they over whom you never bear rule, as those who were not called by your name.t(NUnOh that you would tear the heavens, that you would come down, that the mountains might quake at your presence,U©as when fire kindles the brushwood, [and] the fire causes the waters to boil; to make your name known to your adversaries, that the nations may tremble at your presence!UlWhen you did terrible things which we didn't look for, you came down, the mountains quaked at your presence.UéFor from of old men have not heard, nor perceived by the ear, neither has the eye seen a God besides you, who works for him who waits for him.U∫You meet him who rejoices and works righteousness, those who remember you in your ways: behold, you were angry, and we sinned: in them [have we been] of long time; and shall we be saved?U≠For we have all become as one who is unclean, and all our righteousness is as a polluted garment: and we all fade as a leaf; and our iniquities, like the wind, take us away.U§There is none who calls on your name, who stirs up himself to take hold of you; for you have hid your face from us, and have consumed us by means of our iniquities.UoBut now, Yahweh, you are our Father; we are the clay, and you our potter; and we all are the work of your hand.UkDon't be furious, Yahweh, neither remember iniquity forever: see, look, we beg you, we are all your people.U^Your holy cities are become a wilderness, Zion is become a wilderness, Jerusalem a desolation.UÅOur holy and our beautiful house, where our fathers praised you, is burned with fire; and all our pleasant places are laid waste.UgWill you refrain yourself for these things, Yahweh? will you hold your peace, and afflict us very sore?t(NUïI am inquired of by those who didn't ask; I am found by those who didn't seek me: I said, See me, see me, to a nation that was not called by my name.U|I have spread out my hands all the day to a rebellious people, who walk in a way that is not good, after their own thoughts;Ufa people who provoke me to my face continually, sacrificing in gardens, and burning incense on bricks;UÇwho sit among the graves, and lodge in the secret places; who eat pig's flesh, and broth of abominable things is in their vessels;Uâwho say, Stand by yourself, don't come near to me, for I am holier than you. These are a smoke in my nose, a fire that burns all the day.UwBehold, it is written before me: I will not keep silence, but will recompense, yes, I will recompense into their bosom,U‘your own iniquities, and the iniquities of your fathers together, says Yahweh, who have burned incense on the mountains, and blasphemed me on the hills; therefore will I first measure their work into their bosom.U∏Thus says Yahweh, As the new wine is found in the cluster, and one says, Don't destroy it, for a blessing is in it: so will I do for my servants' sake, that I may not destroy them all.UôI will bring forth a seed out of Jacob, and out of Judah an inheritor of my mountains; and my chosen shall inherit it, and my servants shall dwell there.U}Sharon shall be a fold of flocks, and the valley of Achor a place for herds to lie down in, for my people who have sought me.UÄBut you who forsake Yahweh, who forget my holy mountain, who prepare a table for Fortune, and who fill up mixed wine to Destiny;UÓI will destine you to the sword, and you shall all bow down to the slaughter; because when I called, you 