ore me, says Yahweh, so your seed and your name shall remain.UåIt shall happen, that from one new moon to another, and from one Sabbath to another, shall all flesh come to worship before me, says Yahweh.UŒThey shall go forth, and look on the dead bodies of the men who have transgressed against me: for their worm shall not die, neither shall their fire be quenched; and they shall be an abhorring to all flesh.ttq(UJeremiah(NUfThe words of Jeremiah the son of Hilkiah, of the priests who were in Anathoth in the land of Benjamin:Uzto whom the word of Yahweh came in the days of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah, in the thirteenth year of his reign.U‘It came also in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, to the end of the eleventh year of Zedekiah, the son of Josiah, king of Judah, to the carrying away of Jerusalem captive in the fifth month.U*Now the word of Yahweh came to me, saying,UóBefore I formed you in the belly I knew you, and before you came forth out of the womb I sanctified you; I have appointed you a prophet to the nations.URThen said I, Ah, Lord Yahweh! behold, I don't know how to speak; for I am a child.UëBut Yahweh said to me, Don't say, I am a child; for to whoever I shall send you, you shall go, and whatever I shall command you, you shall speak.UODon't be afraid because of them; for I am with you to deliver you, says Yahweh.UwThen Yahweh put forth his hand, and touched my mouth; and Yahweh said to me, Behold, I have put my words in your mouth:Uùbehold, I have this day set you over the nations and over the kingdoms, to pluck up and to break down and to destroy and to overthrow, to build and to plant.UnMoreover the word of Yahweh came to me, saying, Jeremiah, what see you? I said, I see a rod of an almond tree.USThen said Yahweh to me, You have well seen: for I watch over my word to perform it.UÖThe word of Yahweh came to me the second time, saying, What see you? I said, I see a boiling caldron; and its face is from the north.UcThen Yahweh said to me, Out of the north evil shall break forth on all the inhabitants of the land.T␀␀For, behold, I will call all the families of the kingdoms of the north, says Yahweh; and they shall come, and they shall set everyone his throne at the entrance of the gates of Jerusalem, and against all its walls all around, and against all the cities of Judah.U∑I will utter my judgments against them touching all their wickedness, in that they have forsaken me, and have burned incense to other gods, and worshiped the works of their own hands.UêYou therefore gird up your waist, and arise, and speak to them all that I command you: don't be dismayed at them, lest I dismay you before them.UﬂFor, behold, I have made you this day a fortified city, and an iron pillar, and bronze walls, against the whole land, against the kings of Judah, against its princes, against its priests, and against the people of the land.UuThey shall fight against you; but they shall not prevail against you: for I am with you, says Yahweh, to deliver you.t(NU&The word of Yahweh came to me, saying,UœGo, and cry in the ears of Jerusalem, saying, Thus says Yahweh, I remember for you the kindness of your youth, the love of your weddings; how you went after me in the wilderness, in a land that was not sown.UëIsrael [was] holiness to Yahweh, the first fruits of his increase: all who devour him shall be held guilty; evil shall come on them, says Yahweh.U[Hear you the word of Yahweh, O house of Jacob, and all the families of the house of Israel:Uôthus says Yahweh, What unrighteousness have your fathers found in me, that they have gone far from me, and have walked after vanity, and are become vain?T␀␀Neither said they, Where is Yahweh who brought us up out of the land of Egypt, who led us through the wilderness, through a land of deserts and of pits, through a land of drought and of the shadow of death, through a land that none passed through, and where no man lived?UóI brought you into a plentiful land, to eat its fruit and its goodness; but when you entered, you defiled my land, and made my heritage an abomination.UœThe priests didn't say, Where is Yahweh? and those who handle the law didn't know me: the rulers also transgressed against me, and the prophets prophesied by Baal, and walked after things that do not profit.UeTherefore I will yet contend with you, says Yahweh, and with your children's children will I contend.UÑFor pass over to the islands of Kittim, and see; and send to Kedar, and consider diligently; and see if there has been such a thing.U~Has a nation changed [its] gods, which yet are no gods? but my people have changed their glory for that which does not profit.U_Be astonished, you heavens, at this, and be horribly afraid, be you very desolate, says Yahweh.UüFor my people have committed two evils: they have forsaken me, the spring of living waters, and cut them out cisterns, broken cisterns, that can hold no water.UJIs Israel a servant? is he a native-born [slave]? why is he become a prey?UÄThe young lions have roared on him, and yelled; and they have made his land waste: his cities are burned up, without inhabitant.UNThe children also of Memphis and Tahpanhes have broken the crown of your head.UmHaven't you procured this to yourself, in that you have forsaken Yahweh your God, when he led you by the way?UüNow what have you to do in the way to Egypt, to drink the waters of the Shihor? or what have you to do in the way to Assyria, to drink the waters of the River?UıYour own wickedness shall correct you, and your backsliding shall reprove you: know therefore and see that it is an evil thing and a bitter, that you have forsaken Yahweh your God, and that my fear is not in you, says the Lord, Yahweh of Armies.UæFor of old time I have broken your yoke, and burst your bonds; and you said, I will not serve; for on every high hill and under every green tree you did bow yourself, playing the prostitute.UÜYet I had planted you a noble vine, wholly a right seed: how then are you turned into the degenerate branches of a foreign vine to me?UvFor though you wash yourself with lye, and use much soap, yet your iniquity is marked before me, says the Lord Yahweh.U©How can you say, I am not defiled, I have not gone after the Baals? see your way in the valley, know what you have done: [you are] a swift dromedary traversing her ways;U«a wild donkey used to the wilderness, that snuffs up the wind in her desire; in her occasion who can turn her away? all those who seek her will not weary themselves; in her month they shall find her.UôWithhold your foot from being unshod, and your throat from thirst: but you said, It is in vain; no, for I have loved strangers, and after them will I go.UïAs the thief is ashamed when he is found, so is the house of Israel ashamed; they, their kings, their princes, and their priests, and their prophets;UŒwho tell a stock, You are my father; and to a stone, You have brought me forth: for they have turned their back to me, and not their face; but in the time of their trouble they will say, Arise, and save us.U≤But where are your gods that you have made you? let them arise, if they can save you in the time of your trouble: for according to the number of your cities are your gods, Judah.UPWhy will you contend with me? you all have transgressed against me, says Yahweh.UÑIn vain have I struck your children; they received no correction: your own sword has devoured your prophets, like a destroying lion.U©Generation, see the word of Yahweh. Have I been a wilderness to Israel? or a land of thick darkness? why say my people, We are broken loose; we will come no more to you?UnCan a virgin forget her ornaments, or a bride her attire? yet my people have forgotten me days without number.UbHow trimmest you your way to seek love! therefore even the wicked women have you taught your ways.UìAlso in your skirts is found the blood of the souls of the innocent poor: you did not find them breaking in; but it is because of all these things.UñYet you said, I am innocent; surely his anger is turned away from me. Behold, I will enter into judgment with you, because you say, I have not sinned.UpWhy go you about so much to change your way? you shall be ashamed of Egypt also, as you were ashamed of Assyria.UóFrom there also you shall go forth, with your hands on your head: for Yahweh has rejected those in whom you trust, and you shall not prosper with them.t(NUThey say, If a man put away his wife, and she go from him, and become another man's, will he return to her again? Won't that land be greatly polluted? But you have played the prostitute with many lovers; yet return again to me, says Yahweh.UÊLift up your eyes to the bare heights, and see; where have you not been lain with? By the ways have you sat for them, as an Arabian in the wilderness; and you have polluted the land with your prostitution and with your wickedness.UçTherefore the showers have been withheld, and there has been no latter rain; yet you have a prostitute's forehead, you refused to be ashamed.UPWill you not from this time cry to me, My Father, you are the guide of my youth?UâWill he retain [his anger] forever? will he keep it to the end? Behold, you have spoken and have done evil things, and have had your way.U◊Moreover Yahweh said to me in the days of Josiah the king, Have you seen that which backsliding Israel has done? she is gone up on every high mountain and under every green tree, and there has played the prostitute.UÇI said after she had done all these things, She will return to me; but she didn't return: and her treacherous sister Judah saw it.U·I saw, when, for this very cause that backsliding Israel had committed adultery, I had put her away and given her a bill of divorce, yet treacherous Judah, her sister, didn't fear; but she also went and played the prostitute.UäIt happened through the lightness of her prostitution, that the land was polluted, and she committed adultery with stones and with stocks.U}Yet for all this her treacherous sister Judah has not returned to me with her whole heart, but only in pretense, says Yahweh.U^Yahweh said to me, Backsliding Israel has shown herself more righteous than treacherous Judah.U∆Go, and proclaim these words toward the north, and say, Return, you backsliding Israel, says Yahweh; I will not look in anger on you; for I am merciful, says Yahweh, I will not keep [anger] forever.U»Only acknowledge your iniquity, that you have transgressed against Yahweh your God, and have scattered your ways to the strangers under every green tree, and you have not obeyed my voice, says Yahweh.UõReturn, backsliding children, says Yahweh; for I am a husband to you: and I will take you one of a city, and two of a family, and I will bring you to Zion:Uiand I will give you shepherds according to my heart, who shall feed you with knowledge and understanding.T␀␀It shall come to pass, when you are multiplied and increased in the land, in those days, says Yahweh, they shall say no more, The ark of the covenant of Yahweh; neither shall it come to mind; neither shall they remember it; neither shall they miss it; neither shall it be made any more.U€At that time they shall call Jerusalem the throne of Yahweh; and all the nations shall be gathered to it, to the name of Yahweh, to Jerusalem: neither shall they walk any more after the stubbornness of their evil heart.UªIn those days the house of Judah shall walk with the house of Israel, and they shall come together out of the land of the north to the land that I gave for an inheritance to your fathers.U‘But I said, How I will put you among the children, and give you a pleasant land, a goodly heritage of the armies of the nations! and I said, You shall call me My Father, and shall not turn away from following me.USurely as a wife treacherously departs from her husband, so have you dealt treacherously with me, house of Israel, says Yahweh.U≠A voice is heard on the bare heights, the weeping [and] the petitions of the children of Israel; because they have perverted their way, they have forgotten Yahweh their God.UwReturn, you backsliding children, I will heal your backsliding. Behold, we are come to you; for you are Yahweh our God.UèTruly in vain is [the help that is looked for] from the hills, the tumult on the mountains: truly in Yahweh our God is the salvation of Israel.UäBut the shameful thing has devoured the labor of our fathers from our youth, their flocks and their herds, their sons and their daughters.U—Let us lie down in our shame, and let our confusion cover us; for we have sinned against Yahweh our God, we and our fathers, from our youth even to this day; and we have not obeyed the voice of Yahweh our God.t(NUùIf you will return, Israel, says Yahweh, if you will return to me, and if you will put away your abominations out of my sight; then you shall not be removed;Uùand you shall swear, As Yahweh lives, in truth, in justice, and in righteousness; and the nations shall bless themselves in him, and in him shall they glory.UsFor thus says Yahweh to the men of Judah and to Jerusalem, Break up your fallow ground, and don't sow among thorns.UÂCircumcise yourselves to Yahweh, and take away the foreskins of your heart, you men of Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem; lest my wrath go forth like fire, and burn so that none can quench it, because of the evil of your doings.U´Declare you in Judah, and publish in Jerusalem; and say, Blow you the trumpet in the land: cry aloud and say, Assemble yourselves, and let us go into the fortified cities.UzSet up a standard toward Zion: flee for safety, don't stay; for I will bring evil from the north, and a great destruction.U¬A lion is gone up from his thicket, and a destroyer of nations; he is on his way, he is gone forth from his place, to make your land desolate, that your cities be laid waste, without inhabitant.UmFor this gird you with sackcloth, lament and wail; for the fierce anger of Yahweh hasn't turned back from us.U¥It shall happen