 great destruction.UBThe comely and delicate one, the daughter of Zion, will I cut off.UäShepherds with their flocks shall come to her; they shall pitch their tents against her all around; they shall feed everyone in his place.UêPrepare you war against her; arise, and let us go up at noon. Woe to us! for the day declines, for the shadows of the evening are stretched out.UAArise, and let us go up by night, and let us destroy her palaces.U®For thus has Yahweh of Armies said, Cut down trees, and cast up a mound against Jerusalem: this is the city to be visited; she is wholly oppression in the midst of her.UúAs a well casts forth its waters, so she casts forth her wickedness: violence and destruction is heard in her; before me continually is sickness and wounds.UqBe instructed, Jerusalem, lest my soul be alienated from you; lest I make you a desolation, a land not inhabited.UìThus says Yahweh of Armies, They shall thoroughly glean the remnant of Israel as a vine: turn again your hand as a grape gatherer into the baskets.U∆To whom shall I speak and testify, that they may hear? behold, their ear is uncircumcised, and they can't listen: behold, the word of Yahweh is become to them a reproach; they have no delight in it.U˜Therefore I am full of the wrath of Yahweh; I am weary with holding in: pour it out on the children in the street, and on the assembly of young men together; for even the husband with the wife shall be taken, the aged with him who is full of days.UöTheir houses shall be turned to others, their fields and their wives together; for I will stretch out my hand on the inhabitants of the land, says Yahweh.UöFor from the least of them even to the greatest of them everyone is given to covetousness; and from the prophet even to the priest everyone deals falsely.UcThey have healed also the hurt of my people slightly, saying, Peace, peace; when there is no peace.UÁWere they ashamed when they had committed abomination? nay, they were not at all ashamed, neither could 