 and iron: they all of them deal corruptly.UÅThe bellows blow fiercely; the lead is consumed of the fire: in vain do they go on refining; for the wicked are not plucked away.UEMen will call them rejected silver, because Yahweh has rejected them.t(NU3The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh, saying,U•Stand in the gate of Yahweh's house, and proclaim there this word, and say, Hear the word of Yahweh, all you of Judah, who enter in at these gates to worship Yahweh.U|Thus says Yahweh of Armies, the God of Israel, Amend your ways and your doings, and I will cause you to dwell in this place.UtDon't you trust in lying words, saying, The temple of Yahweh, the temple of Yahweh, the temple of Yahweh, are these.UxFor if you thoroughly amend your ways and your doings; if you thoroughly execute justice between a man and his neighbor;Uüif you don't oppress the foreigner, the fatherless, and the widow, and don't shed innocent blood in this place, neither walk after other gods to your own hurt:Utthen will I cause you to dwell in this place, in the land that I gave to your fathers, from of old even forevermore.U4Behold, you trust in lying words, that can't profit.UåWill you steal, murder, and commit adultery, and swear falsely, and burn incense to Baal, and walk after other gods that you have not known,Uäand come and stand before me in this house, which is called by my name, and say, We are delivered; that you may do all these abominations?U~Is this house, which is called by my name, become a den of robbers in your eyes? Behold, I, even I, have seen it, says Yahweh.UûBut go you now to my place which was in Shiloh, where I caused my name to dwell at the first, and see what I did to it for the wickedness of my people Israel.U®Now, because you have done all these works, says Yahweh, and I spoke to you, rising up early and speaking, but you didn't hear; and I called you, but you didn't answer:Uûtherefore will I do to the house which is called by my name, in which you trust, and to the