ore thus says Yahweh concerning the men of Anathoth, who seek your life, saying, You shall not prophesy in the name of Yahweh, that you not die by our hand;Uõtherefore thus says Yahweh of Armies, Behold, I will punish them: the young men shall die by the sword; their sons and their daughters shall die by famine;Uwand there shall be no remnant to them: for I will bring evil on the men of Anathoth, even the year of their visitation.t(NU∏Righteous are you, Yahweh, when I contend with you; yet would I reason the cause with you: why does the way of the wicked prosper? why are all they at ease who deal very treacherously?UêYou have planted them, yes, they have taken root; they grow, yes, they bring forth fruit: you are near in their mouth, and far from their heart.UôBut you, Yahweh, know me; you see me, and try my heart toward you: pull them out like sheep for the slaughter, and prepare them for the day of slaughter.U’How long shall the land mourn, and the herbs of the whole country wither? for the wickedness of those who dwell therein, the animals are consumed, and the birds; because they said, He shall not see our latter end.U¿If you have run with the footmen, and they have wearied you, then how can you contend with horses? and though in a land of peace you are secure, yet how will you do in the pride of the Jordan?U∆For even your brothers, and the house of your father, even they have dealt treacherously with you; even they have cried aloud after you: don't believe them, though they speak beautiful words to you.UI have forsaken my house, I have cast off my heritage; I have given the dearly beloved of my soul into the hand of her enemies.UvMy heritage is become to me as a lion in the forest: she has uttered her voice against me; therefore I have hated her.U£Is my heritage to me as a speckled bird of prey? are the birds of prey against her all around? go you, assemble all the animals of the field, bring them to devour.UçMany shepherds have destroyed my vineyard, they have trodden my portion under foot, they have made my pleasant portion a desolate wilderness.UÇThey have made it a desolation; it mourns to me, being desolate; the whole land is made desolate, because no man lays it to heart.U≤Destroyers are come on all the bare heights in the wilderness; for the sword of Yahweh devours from the one end of the land even to the other end of the land: no flesh has peace.U≥They have sown wheat, and have reaped thorns; they have put themselves to pain, and profit nothing: and you shall be ashamed of your fruits, because of the fierce anger of Yahweh.U‚Thus says Yahweh against all my evil neighbors, who touch the inheritance which I have caused my people Israel to inherit: behold, I will pluck them up from off their land, and will pluck up the house of Judah from among them.U±It shall happen, after that I have plucked them up, I will return and have compassion on them; and I will bring them again, every man to his heritage, and every man to his land.U“It shall happen, if they will diligently learn the ways of my people, to swear by my name, As Yahweh lives; even as they taught my people to swear by Baal; then shall they be built up in the midst of my people.UhBut if they will not hear, then will I pluck up that nation, plucking up and destroying it, says Yahweh.t(NUjThus says Yahweh to me, Go, and buy you a linen belt, and put it on your waist, and don't put it in water.UKSo I bought a belt according to the word of Yahweh, and put it on my waist.U6The word of Yahweh came to me the second time, saying,UÖTake the belt that you have bought, which is on your waist, and arise, go to the Euphrates, and hide it there in a cleft of the rock.U?So I went, and hid it by the Euphrates, as Yahweh commanded me.UìIt happened after many days, that Yahweh said to me, Arise, go to the Euphrates, and take the belt from there, which I commanded you to hide there.UõThen I went to the Euphrates, and dug, and took the belt from the place where I had hid it; and behold, the belt was marred, it was profitable for nothing.U+Then the word of Yahweh came to me, saying,UdThus says Yahweh, After this manner will I mar the pride of Judah, and the great pride of Jerusalem.U⁄This evil people, who refuse to hear my words, who walk in the stubbornness of their heart, and are gone after other gods to serve them, and to worship them, shall even be as this belt, which is profitable for nothing.T␀␀For as the belt cleaves to the waist of a man, so have I caused to cleave to me the whole house of Israel and the whole house of Judah, says Yahweh; that they may be to me for a people, and for a name, and for a praise, and for a glory: but they would not hear.UÿTherefore you shall speak to them this word: Thus says Yahweh, the God of Israel, Every bottle shall be filled with wine: and they shall tell you, Do we not certainly know that every bottle shall be filled with wine?UÊThen you shall tell them, Thus says Yahweh, Behold, I will fill all the inhabitants of this land, even the kings who sit on David's throne, and the priests, and the prophets, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, with drunkenness.U´I will dash them one against another, even the fathers and the sons together, says Yahweh: I will not pity, nor spare, nor have compassion, that I should not destroy them.U>Hear you, and give ear; don't be proud; for Yahweh has spoken.UÃGive glory to Yahweh your God, before he cause darkness, and before your feet stumble on the dark mountains, and, while you look for light, he turn it into the shadow of death, and make it gross darkness.U©But if you will not hear it, my soul shall weep in secret for [your] pride; and my eye shall weep sore, and run down with tears, because Yahweh's flock is taken captive.UãSay you to the king and to the queen mother, Humble yourselves, sit down; for your headdresses are come down, even the crown of your glory.UëThe cities of the South are shut up, and there is none to open them: Judah is carried away captive, all of it; it is wholly carried away captive.UvLift up your eyes, and see those who come from the north: where is the flock that was given you, your beautiful flock?U≠What will you say, when he shall set over you as head those whom you have yourself taught to be friends to you? shall not sorrows take hold of you, as of a woman in travail?UòIf you say in your heart, Why are these things come on me? for the greatness of your iniquity are your skirts uncovered, and your heels suffer violence.UvCan the Ethiopian change his skin, or the leopard his spots? then may you also do good, who are accustomed to do evil.U^Therefore will I scatter them, as the stubble that passes away, by the wind of the wilderness.U|This is your lot, the portion measured to you from me, says Yahweh; because you have forgotten me, and trusted in falsehood.UTTherefore will I also uncover your skirts on your face, and your shame shall appear.U“I have seen your abominations, even your adulteries, and your neighing, the lewdness of your prostitution, on the hills in the field. Woe to you, Jerusalem! you will not be made clean; how long shall it yet be?t(NU@The word of Yahweh that came to Jeremiah concerning the drought.UkJudah mourns, and its gates languish, they sit in black on the ground; and the cry of Jerusalem is gone up.U√Their nobles send their little ones to the waters: they come to the cisterns, and find no water; they return with their vessels empty; they are disappointed and confounded, and cover their heads.UÉBecause of the ground which is cracked, because no rain has been in the land, the plowmen are disappointed, they cover their heads.U\Yes, the hind also in the field calves, and forsakes [her young], because there is no grass.UyThe wild donkeys stand on the bare heights, they pant for air like jackals; their eyes fail, because there is no herbage.UãThough our iniquities testify against us, work you for your name's sake, Yahweh; for our backslidings are many; we have sinned against you.U†