l go forth into captivity, his priests and his princes together.UóThe destroyer shall come on every city, and no city shall escape; the valley also shall perish, and the plain shall be destroyed; as Yahweh has spoken.U~Give wings to Moab, that she may fly and get her away: and her cities shall become a desolation, without any to dwell therein.UkCursed be he who does the work of Yahweh negligently; and cursed be he who keeps back his sword from blood.U€Moab has been at ease from his youth, and he has settled on his lees, and has not been emptied from vessel to vessel, neither has he gone into captivity: therefore his taste remains in him, and his scent is not changed.UºTherefore, behold, the days come, says Yahweh, that I will send to him those who pour off, and they shall pour him off; and they shall empty his vessels, and break their bottles in pieces.U`Moab shall be ashamed of Chemosh, as the house of Israel was ashamed of Bethel their confidence.U<How say you, We are mighty men, and valiant men for the war?U°Moab is laid waste, and they are gone up into his cities, and his chosen young men are gone down to the slaughter, says the King, whose name is Yahweh of Armies.UFThe calamity of Moab is near to come, and his affliction hurries fast.U~All you who are around him, bemoan him, and all you who know his name; say, How is the strong staff broken, the beautiful rod!U§You daughter who dwells in Dibon, come down from your glory, and sit in thirst; for the destroyer of Moab is come up against you, he has destroyed your strongholds.UrInhabitant of Aroer, stand by the way, and watch: ask him who flees, and her who escapes; say, What has been done?UmMoab is disappointed; for it is broken down: wail and cry; tell you it by the Arnon, that Moab is laid waste.UPJudgment is come on the plain country, on Holon, and on Jahzah, and on Mephaath,U2and on Dibon, and on Nebo, and on Beth Diblathaim,U7and on Kiriathaim, and on Beth Gamul, and on Beth Meon,UVand on Kerioth, and on Bozrah, and on all the cities of the land of Moab, far or near.U@The horn of Moab is cut off, and his arm is broken, says Yahweh.UÑMake you him drunken; for he magnified himself against Yahweh: and Moab shall wallow in his vomit, and he also shall be in derision.UtFor wasn't Israel a derision to you? was he found among thieves? for as often as you speak of him, you wag the head.UáYou inhabitants of Moab, leave the cities, and dwell in the rock; and be like the dove that makes her nest over the mouth of the abyss.UèWe have heard of the pride of Moab, [that] he is very proud; his loftiness, and his pride, and his arrogance, and the haughtiness of his heart.UUI know his wrath, says Yahweh, that it is nothing; his boastings have worked nothing.UlTherefore will I wail for Moab; yes, I will cry out for all Moab: for the men of Kir Heres shall they mourn.U’With more than the weeping of Jazer will I weep for you, vine of Sibmah: your branches passed over the sea, they reached even to the sea of Jazer: on your summer fruits and on your vintage the destroyer is fallen.UÀGladness and joy is taken away from the fruitful field and from the land of Moab; and I have caused wine to cease from the wine presses: none shall tread with shouting; the shouting shall be no shouting.UΩFrom the cry of Heshbon even to Elealeh, even to Jahaz have they uttered their voice, from Zoar even to Horonaim, to Eglath Shelishiyah: for the waters of Nimrim also shall become desolate.U}Moreover I will cause to cease in Moab, says Yahweh, him who offers in the high place, and him who burns incense to his gods.UüTherefore my heart sounds for Moab like pipes, and my heart sounds like pipes for the men of Kir Heres: therefore the abundance that he has gotten is perished.UkFor every head is bald, and every beard clipped: on all the hands are cuttings, and on the waist sackcloth.UõOn all the housetops of Moab and in its streets there is lamentation every where; for I have broken Moab like a vessel in which none 