stitution of her sister.UóShe doted on the Assyrians, governors and rulers, [her] neighbors, clothed most gorgeously, horsemen riding on horses, all of them desirable young men.U3I saw that she was defiled; they both took one way.U|She increased her prostitution; for she saw men portrayed on the wall, the images of the Chaldeans portrayed with vermilion,U¥girded with girdles on their waists, with flowing turbans on their heads, all of them princes to look on, after the likeness of the Babylonians in Chaldea, the land of their birth.UTAs soon as she saw them she doted on them, and sent messengers to them into Chaldea.U•The Babylonians came to her into the bed of love, and they defiled her with their prostitution, and she was polluted with them, and her soul was alienated from them.UìSo she uncovered her prostitution, and uncovered her nakedness: then my soul was alienated from her, like as my soul was alienated from her sister.UÑYet she multiplied her prostitution, remembering the days of her youth, in which she had played the prostitute in the land of Egypt.UrShe doted on their paramours, whose flesh is as the flesh of donkeys, and whose issue is like the issue of horses.UÉThus you called to memory the lewdness of your youth, in the handling of your bosom by the Egyptians for the breasts of your youth.U≥Therefore, Oholibah, thus says the Lord Yahweh: Behold, I will raise up your lovers against you, from whom your soul is alienated, and I will bring them against you on every side:U—the Babylonians and all the Chaldeans, Pekod and Shoa and Koa, [and] all the Assyrians with them; desirable young men, governors and rulers all of them, princes and men of renown, all of them riding on horses.T␀␀They shall come against you with weapons, chariots, and wagons, and with a company of peoples; they shall set themselves against you with buckler and shield and helmet all around; and I will commit the judgment to them, and they shall judge you according to their judgments.UˇI will set my jealousy against you, and they shall deal with you in fury; they shall take away your nose and your ears; and your residue shall fall by the sword: they shall take your sons and your daughters; and your residue shall be devoured by the fire.UOThey shall also strip you of your clothes, and take away your beautiful jewels.U∑Thus will I make your lewdness to cease from you, and your prostitution [brought] from the land of Egypt; so that you shall not lift up your eyes to them, nor remember Egypt any more.UñFor thus says the Lord Yahweh: Behold, I will deliver you into the hand of them whom you hate, into the hand of them from whom your soul is alienated;U‘and they shall deal with you in hatred, and shall take away all your labor, and shall leave you naked and bare; and the nakedness of your prostitution shall be uncovered, both your lewdness and your prostitution.UãThese things shall be done to you, because you have played the prostitute after the nations, and because you are polluted with their idols.UXYou have walked in the way of your sister; therefore will I give her cup into your hand.UñThus says the Lord Yahweh: You will drink of your sister's cup, which is deep and large; you will be ridiculed and held in derision; it contains much.UÇYou shall be filled with drunkenness and sorrow, with the cup of astonishment and desolation, with the cup of your sister Samaria.UûYou shall even drink it and drain it out, and you shall gnaw the broken pieces of it, and shall tear your breasts; for I have spoken it, says the Lord Yahweh.UûTherefore thus says the Lord Yahweh: Because you have forgotten me, and cast me behind your back, therefore bear you also your lewdness and your prostitution.UtYahweh said moreover to me: Son of man, will you judge Oholah and Oholibah? then declare to them their abominations.U‡For they have committed adultery, and blood is in their hands; and with their idols have they committed adultery; and they have also caused their sons, whom they 