e day: the king of Babylon drew close to Jerusalem this same day.UéUtter a parable to the rebellious house, and tell them, Thus says the Lord Yahweh, Set on the caldron, set it on, and also pour water into it:Umgather its pieces into it, even every good piece, the thigh, and the shoulder; fill it with the choice bones.UòTake the choice of the flock, and also a pile [of wood] for the bones under [the caldron]; make it boil well; yes, let its bones be boiled in its midst.U¬Therefore thus says the Lord Yahweh: Woe to the bloody city, to the caldron whose rust is therein, and whose rust is not gone out of it! take out of it piece after piece; No lot is fallen on it.U{For her blood is in the midst of her; she set it on the bare rock; she didn't pour it on the ground, to cover it with dust.U{That it may cause wrath to come up to take vengeance, I have set her blood on the bare rock, that it should not be covered.U]Therefore thus says the Lord Yahweh: Woe to the bloody city! I also will make the pile great.UpHeap on the wood, make the fire hot, boil well the flesh, and make thick the broth, and let the bones be burned.UóThen set it empty on its coals, that it may be hot, and its brass may burn, and that its filthiness may be molten in it, that its rust may be consumed.UyShe has wearied [herself] with toil; yet her great rust doesn't go forth out of her; her rust doesn't [go forth] by fire.UøIn your filthiness is lewdness: because I have cleansed you and you weren't cleansed, you shall not be cleansed from your filthiness any more, until I have caused my wrath toward you to rest.U‡I, Yahweh, have spoken it: it shall happen, and I will do it: I will not go back, neither will I spare, neither will I repent; according to your ways, and according to your doings, shall they judge you, says the Lord Yahweh.U+Also the word of Yahweh came to me, saying,UòSon of man, behold, I take away from you the desire of your eyes with a stroke: yet you shall neither mourn nor weep, neither shall your tears run down.U¶Sigh, but not aloud, make no mourning for the dead; bind your headdress on you, and put your shoes on your feet, and don't cover your lips, and don't eat men's bread.UoSo I spoke to the people in the morning; and at even my wife died; and I did in the morning as I was commanded.UUThe people said to me, Won't you tell us what these things are to us, that you do so?U;Then I said to them, The word of Yahweh came to me, saying,T␀␀Speak to the house of Israel, Thus says the Lord Yahweh: Behold, I will profane my sanctuary, the pride of your power, the desire of your eyes, and that which your soul pities; and your sons and your daughters whom you have left behind shall fall by the sword.UUYou shall do as I have done: you shall not cover your lips, nor eat the bread of men.U¶Your tires shall be on your heads, and your shoes on your feet: you shall not mourn nor weep; but you shall pine away in your iniquities, and moan one toward another.UíThus shall Ezekiel be to you a sign; according to all that he has done you will do: when this comes, then you will know that I am the Lord Yahweh.UÃYou, son of man, shall it not be in the day when I take from them their strength, the joy of their glory, the desire of their eyes, and that whereupon they set their heart, their sons and their daughters,UZthat in that day he who escapes shall come to you, to cause you to hear it with your ears?U¨In that day your mouth will be opened to him who has escaped, and you shall speak, and be no more mute: so you will be a sign to them; and they shall know that I am Yahweh.t(NU&The word of Yahweh came to me, saying,URSon of man, set your face toward the children of Ammon, and prophesy against them:T␀␀and tell the children of Ammon, Hear the word of the Lord Yahweh: Thus says the Lord Yahweh, Because you said, Aha, against my sanctuary, when it was profaned; and against the land of Israel, when it was made desolate; and against the house of Judah, when they went into captivity:U‹therefore, behold, I will deliver you to the children of the east for a possession, and they shall set their encampments in you, and make their dwellings in you; they shall eat your fruit, and they shall drink your milk.UÇI will make Rabbah a stable for camels, and the children of Ammon a resting place for flocks: and you shall know that I am Yahweh.U©For thus says the Lord Yahweh: Because you have clapped your hands, and stamped with the feet, and rejoiced with all the despite of your soul against the land of Israel;Uˇtherefore, behold, I have stretched out my hand on you, and will deliver you for a spoil to the nations; and I will cut you off from the peoples, and I will cause you to perish out of the countries: I will destroy you; and you shall know that I am Yahweh.UiThus says the Lord Yahweh: Because Moab and Seir say, Behold, the house of Judah is like all the nations;U±therefore, behold, I will open the side of Moab from the cities, from his cities which are on his frontiers, the glory of the country, Beth Jeshimoth, Baal Meon, and Kiriathaim,UÆto the children of the east, [to go] against the children of Ammon; and I will give them for a possession, that the children of Ammon may not be remembered among the nations.UKand I will execute judgments on Moab; and they shall know that I am Yahweh.UôThus says the Lord Yahweh: Because Edom has dealt against the house of Judah by taking vengeance, and has greatly offended, and revenged himself on them;U≈therefore thus says the Lord Yahweh, I will stretch out my hand on Edom, and will cut off man and animal from it; and I will make it desolate from Teman; even to Dedan shall they fall by the sword.U√I will lay my vengeance on Edom by the hand of my people Israel; and they shall do in Edom according to my anger and according to my wrath; and they shall know my vengeance, says the Lord Yahweh.UôThus says the Lord Yahweh: Because the Philistines have dealt by revenge, and have taken vengeance with despite of soul t