use of his God.UÖThey have deeply corrupted themselves, as in the days of Gibeah. He will remember their iniquity. He will punish them for their sins.U˜I found Israel like grapes in the wilderness. I saw your fathers as the first ripe in the fig tree at its first season; but they came to Baal Peor, and consecrated themselves to the shameful thing, and became abominable like that which they loved.UrAs for Ephraim, their glory will fly away like a bird. There will be no birth, none with child, and no conception.UêThough they bring up their children, yet I will bereave them, so that not a man shall be left. Indeed, woe also to them when I depart from them!UuI have seen Ephraim, like Tyre, planted in a pleasant place; but Ephraim will bring out his children to the murderer.USGive them--Yahweh what will you give? Give them a miscarrying womb and dry breasts.Uø"All their wickedness is in Gilgal; for there I hated them. Because of the wickedness of their deeds I will drive them out of my house! I will love them no more. All their princes are rebels.UìEphraim is struck. Their root has dried up. They will bear no fruit. Even though they bring forth, yet I will kill the beloved ones of their womb."UmMy God will cast them away, because they did not listen to him; and they will be wanderers among the nations.t(NUøIsrael is a luxuriant vine that puts forth his fruit. According to the abundance of his fruit he has multiplied his altars. As their land has prospered, they have adorned their sacred stones.UzTheir heart is divided. Now they will be found guilty. He will demolish their altars. He will destroy their sacred stones.UkSurely now they will say, "We have no king; for we don't fear Yahweh; and the king, what can he do for us?"UâThey make promises, swearing falsely in making covenants. Therefore judgment springs up like poisonous weeds in the furrows of the field.U…The inhabitants of Samaria will be in terror for the calves of Beth Aven; for its people will mourn over it, Alo