h blood, and establishes a city by iniquity!UvBehold, isn't it of Yahweh of Armies that the peoples labor for the fire, and the nations weary themselves for vanity?UdFor the earth will be filled with the knowledge of the glory of Yahweh, as the waters cover the sea.Uá"Woe to him who gives his neighbor drink, pouring your inflaming wine until they are drunk, so that you may gaze at their naked bodies!U™You are filled with shame, and not glory. You will also drink, and be exposed! The cup of Yahweh's right hand will come around to you, and disgrace will cover your glory.U›For the violence done to Lebanon will overwhelm you, and the destruction of the animals, which made them afraid; because of men's blood, and for the violence done to the land, to every city and to those who dwell in them.Uµ"What value does the engraved image have, that its maker has engraved it; the molten image, even the teacher of lies, that he who fashions its form trusts in it, to make mute idols?U≥Woe to him who says to the wood, 'Awake!' or to the mute stone, 'Arise!' Shall this teach? Behold, it is overlaid with gold and silver, and there is no breath at all in its midst.UJBut Yahweh is in his holy temple. Let all the earth be silent before him!"t(NU;A prayer of Habakkuk, the prophet, set to victorious music.U∫Yahweh, I have heard of your fame. I stand in awe of your deeds, Yahweh. Renew your work in the midst of the years. In the midst of the years make it known. In wrath, you remember mercy.U{God came from Teman, the Holy One from Mount Paran. Selah.  His glory covered the heavens, and his praise filled the earth.UVHis splendor is like the sunrise. Rays shine from his hand, where his power is hidden.U9Plague went before him, and pestilence followed his feet.UüHe stood, and shook the earth. He looked, and made the nations tremble. The ancient mountains were crumbled. The age-old hills collapsed. His ways are eternal.UVI saw the tents of Cushan in affliction. The dwellings of the land of Midia