selves against the people of Yahweh of Armies.UüYahweh will be awesome to them, for he will famish all the gods of the land. Men will worship him, everyone from his place, even all the shores of the nations.U2You Cushites also, you will be killed by my sword.UÅHe will stretch out his hand against the north, destroy Assyria, and will make Nineveh a desolation, and dry like the wilderness.U˛Herds will lie down in the midst of her, all the animals of the nations. Both the pelican and the porcupine will lodge in its capitals. Their calls will echo through the windows. Desolation will be in the thresholds, for he has laid bare the cedar beams.UÓThis is the joyous city that lived carelessly, that said in her heart, "I am, and there is none besides me." How she has become a desolation, a place for animals to lie down in! Everyone who passes by her will hiss, and shake their fists.t(NU?Woe to her who is rebellious and polluted, the oppressing city!UvShe didn't obey the voice. She didn't receive correction. She didn't trust in Yahweh. She didn't draw near to her God.UxHer princes in the midst of her are roaring lions. Her judges are evening wolves. They leave nothing until the next day.U~Her prophets are arrogant and treacherous people. Her priests have profaned the sanctuary. They have done violence to the law.UúYahweh, in the midst of her, is righteous. He will do no wrong. Every morning he brings his justice to light. He doesn't fail, but the unjust know no shame.U«I have cut off nations. Their battlements are desolate. I have made their streets waste, so that no one passes by. Their cities are destroyed, so that there is no man, so that there is no inhabitant.UΩI said, "Just fear me. Receive correction, so that her dwelling won't be cut off, according to all that I have appointed concerning her." But they rose early and corrupted all their doings.T␀␀"Therefore wait for me," says Yahweh, "until the day that I rise up to the prey, for my determination is to gather the na