art is far from me.UIAnd in vain do they worship me, teaching as doctrine rules made by men.'"UCHe summoned the multitude, and said to them, "Hear, and understand.UyThat which enters into the mouth doesn't defile the man; but that which proceeds out of the mouth, this defiles the man."UvThen the disciples came, and said to him, "Do you know that the Pharisees were offended, when they heard this saying?"UUBut he answered, "Every plant which my heavenly Father didn't plant will be uprooted.UoLeave them alone. They are blind guides of the blind. If the blind guide the blind, both will fall into a pit."U0Peter answered him, "Explain the parable to us."U1So Jesus said, "Do you also still not understand?UgDon't you understand that whatever goes into the mouth passes into the belly, and then out of the body?U]But the things which proceed out of the mouth come out of the heart, and they defile the man.UzFor out of the heart come forth evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, sexual sins, thefts, false testimony, and blasphemies.UbThese are the things which defile the man; but to eat with unwashed hands doesn't defile the man."UJJesus went out from there, and withdrew into the region of Tyre and Sidon.UòBehold, a Canaanite woman came out from those borders, and cried, saying, "Have mercy on me, Lord, you son of David! My daughter is severely demonized!"UsBut he answered her not a word. His disciples came and begged him, saying, "Send her away; for she cries after us."UUBut he answered, "I wasn't sent to anyone but the lost sheep of the house of Israel."U8But she came and worshiped him, saying, "Lord, help me."U_But he answered, "It is not appropriate to take the children's bread and throw it to the dogs."UaBut she said, "Yes, Lord, but even the dogs eat the crumbs which fall from their masters' table."UàThen Jesus answered her, "Woman, great is your faith! Be it done to you even as you desire." And her daughter was healed from that hour.UkJesus departed there, and came near to th