ory of the Father, and of the holy angels.UàBut I tell you the truth: There are some of those who stand here, who will in no way taste of death, until they see the Kingdom of God."UÜIt happened about eight days after these sayings, that he took with him Peter, John, and James, and went up onto the mountain to pray.UfAs he was praying, the appearance of his face was altered, and his clothing became white and dazzling.UABehold, two men were talking with him, who were Moses and Elijah,Uawho appeared in glory, and spoke of his departure, which he was about to accomplish at Jerusalem.UîNow Peter and those who were with him were heavy with sleep, but when they were fully awake, they saw his glory, and the two men who stood with him.U”It happened, as they were parting from him, that Peter said to Jesus, "Master, it is good for us to be here. Let's make three tents: one for you, and one for Moses, and one for Elijah," not knowing what he said.UtWhile he said these things, a cloud came and overshadowed them, and they were afraid as they entered into the cloud.UOA voice came out of the cloud, saying, "This is my beloved Son. Listen to him!"UÇWhen the voice came, Jesus was found alone. They were silent, and told no one in those days any of the things which they had seen.UgIt happened on the next day, when they had come down from the mountain, that a great multitude met him.UpBehold, a man from the crowd called out, saying, "Teacher, I beg you to look at my son, for he is my only child.UêBehold, a spirit takes him, he suddenly cries out, and it convulses him so that he foams, and it hardly departs from him, bruising him severely.U;I begged your disciples to cast it out, and they couldn't."UyJesus answered, "Faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you and bear with you? Bring your son here."U´While he was still coming, the demon threw him down and convulsed him violently. But Jesus rebuked the unclean spirit, and healed the boy, and gave him back to his fathe