ver rejects me rejects him who sent me."U^The seventy returned with joy, saying, "Lord, even the demons are subject to us in your name!"UGHe said to them, "I saw Satan having fallen like lightning from heaven.UáBehold, I give you authority to tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the power of the enemy. Nothing will in any way hurt you.U}Nevertheless, don't rejoice in this, that the spirits are subject to you, but rejoice that your names are written in heaven."T␀␀In that same hour Jesus rejoiced in the Holy Spirit, and said, "I thank you, O Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that you have hidden these things from the wise and understanding, and revealed them to little children. Yes, Father, for so it was well-pleasing in your sight."U‡Turning to the disciples, he said, "All things have been delivered to me by my Father. No one knows who the Son is, except the Father, and who the Father is, except the Son, and he to whomever the Son desires to reveal him."UeTurning to the disciples, he said privately, "Blessed are the eyes which see the things that you see,Ußfor I tell you that many prophets and kings desired to see the things which you see, and didn't see them, and to hear the things which you hear, and didn't hear them."UmBehold, a certain lawyer stood up and tested him, saying, "Teacher, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?"UAHe said to him, "What is written in the law? How do you read it?"UßHe answered, "You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, with all your strength, and with all your mind; and your neighbor as yourself."UJHe said to him, "You have answered correctly. Do this, and you will live."UGBut he, desiring to justify himself, asked Jesus, "Who is my neighbor?"U¨Jesus answered, "A certain man was going down from Jerusalem to Jericho, and he fell among robbers, who both stripped him and beat him, and departed, leaving him half dead.UdBy chance a certain priest was going down that way. When he saw him, he passed