eeking to catch him in something he might say, that they might accuse him.t(NUŸMeanwhile, when a multitude of many thousands had gathered together, so much so that they trampled on each other, he began to tell his disciples first of all, "Beware of the yeast of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy.U_But there is nothing covered up, that will not be revealed, nor hidden, that will not be known.UßTherefore whatever you have said in the darkness will be heard in the light. What you have spoken in the ear in the inner chambers will be proclaimed on the housetops.Ur"I tell you, my friends, don't be afraid of those who kill the body, and after that have no more that they can do.UáBut I will warn you whom you should fear. Fear him, who after he has killed, has power to cast into Gehenna. Yes, I tell you, fear him.UV"Aren't five sparrows sold for two assaria coins? Not one of them is forgotten by God.UvBut the very hairs of your head are all numbered. Therefore don't be afraid. You are of more value than many sparrows.Uq"I tell you, everyone who confesses me before men, him will the Son of Man also confess before the angels of God;U`but he who denies me in the presence of men will be denied in the presence of the angels of God.UâEveryone who speaks a word against the Son of Man will be forgiven, but those who blaspheme against the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven.UèWhen they bring you before the synagogues, the rulers, and the authorities, don't be anxious how or what you will answer, or what you will say;UHfor the Holy Spirit will teach you in that same hour what you must say."U_One of the multitude said to him, "Teacher, tell my brother to divide the inheritance with me."UIBut he said to him, "Man, who made me a judge or an arbitrator over you?"UëHe said to them, "Beware! Keep yourselves from covetousness, for a man's life doesn't consist of the abundance of the things which he possesses."U_He spoke a parable to them, saying, "The ground of a certain rich man brought forth a