ed up, and denied in the presence of Pilate, when he had determined to release him.UYBut you denied the Holy and Righteous One, and asked for a murderer to be granted to you,UXand killed the Prince of life, whom God raised from the dead, to which we are witnesses.U¥By faith in his name, his name has made this man strong, whom you see and know. Yes, the faith which is through him has given him this perfect soundness in the presence of you all.UO"Now, brothers, I know that you did this in ignorance, as did also your rulers.UrBut the things which God announced by the mouth of all his prophets, that Christ should suffer, he thus fulfilled.Uè"Repent therefore, and turn again, that your sins may be blotted out, so that there may come times of refreshing from the presence of the Lord,UCand that he may send Christ Jesus, who was ordained for you before,UÇwhom heaven must receive until the times of restoration of all things, which God spoke long ago by the mouth of his holy prophets.UµFor Moses indeed said to the fathers, 'The Lord God will raise up a prophet for you from among your brothers, like me. You shall listen to him in all things whatever he says to you.UrIt will be, that every soul that will not listen to that prophet will be utterly destroyed from among the people.'UyYes, and all the prophets from Samuel and those who followed after, as many as have spoken, they also told of these days.U´You are the children of the prophets, and of the covenant which God made with our fathers, saying to Abraham, 'In your seed will all the families of the earth be blessed.'UÖGod, having raised up his servant, Jesus, sent him to you first, to bless you, in turning away everyone of you from your wickedness."t(NUfAs they spoke to the people, the priests and the captain of the temple and the Sadducees came to them,Ubbeing upset because they taught the people and proclaimed in Jesus the resurrection from the dead.U\They laid hands on them, and put them in custody until the next day, for