 apostles' feet, and distribution was made to each, according as anyone had need.UàJoses, who by the apostles was surnamed Barnabas (which is, being interpreted, Son of Encouragement), a Levite, a man of Cyprus by race,UQhaving a field, sold it, and brought the money and laid it at the apostles' feet.t(NULBut a certain man named Ananias, with Sapphira, his wife, sold a possession,UÄand kept back part of the price, his wife also being aware of it, and brought a certain part, and laid it at the apostles' feet.UÑBut Peter said, "Ananias, why has Satan filled your heart to lie to the Holy Spirit, and to keep back part of the price of the land?UªWhile you kept it, didn't it remain your own? After it was sold, wasn't it in your power? How is it that you have conceived this thing in your heart? You haven't lied to men, but to God."U`Ananias, hearing these words, fell down and died. Great fear came on all who heard these things.UPThe young men arose and wrapped him up, and they carried him out and buried him.UJAbout three hours later, his wife, not knowing what had happened, came in.UbPeter answered her, "Tell me whether you sold the land for so much." She said, "Yes, for so much."UƒBut Peter asked her, "How is it that you have agreed together to tempt the Spirit of the Lord? Behold, the feet of those who have buried your husband are at the door, and they will carry you out."UíShe fell down immediately at his feet, and died. The young men came in and found her dead, and they carried her out and buried her by her husband.UIGreat fear came on the whole assembly, and on all who heard these things.UÅBy the hands of the apostles many signs and wonders were done among the people. They were all with one accord in Solomon's porch.UENone of the rest dared to join them, however the people honored them.UHMore believers were added to the Lord, multitudes of both men and women.UßThey even carried out the sick into the streets, and laid them on cots and mattresses, so that as Peter came 