f the Egyptians. He was mighty in his words and works.UfBut when he was forty years old, it came into his heart to visit his brothers, the children of Israel.UkSeeing one of them suffer wrong, he defended him, and avenged him who was oppressed, striking the Egyptian.UxHe supposed that his brothers understood that God, by his hand, was giving them deliverance; but they didn't understand.Uú"The day following, he appeared to them as they fought, and urged them to be at peace again, saying, 'Sirs, you are brothers. Why do you wrong one another?'UeBut he who did his neighbor wrong pushed him away, saying, 'Who made you a ruler and a judge over us?U>Do you want to kill me, as you killed the Egyptian yesterday?'UoMoses fled at this saying, and became a stranger in the land of Midian, where he became the father of two sons.UÜ"When forty years were fulfilled, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in the wilderness of Mount Sinai, in a flame of fire in a bush.UfWhen Moses saw it, he wondered at the sight. As he came close to see, a voice of the Lord came to him,U'I am the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.' Moses trembled, and dared not look.UhThe Lord said to him, 'Take your sandals off of your feet, for the place where you stand is holy ground.U®I have surely seen the affliction of my people that is in Egypt, and have heard their groaning. I have come down to deliver them. Now come, I will send you into Egypt.'U∑"This Moses, whom they refused, saying, 'Who made you a ruler and a judge?'--God has sent him as both a ruler and a deliverer by the hand of the angel who appeared to him in the bush.UwThis man led them out, having worked wonders and signs in Egypt, in the Red Sea, and in the wilderness for forty years.UçThis is that Moses, who said to the children of Israel, 'The Lord our God will raise up a prophet for you from among your brothers, like me.'U¶This is he who was in the assembly in the wilderness with the angel that spok