t, and they gnashed at him with their teeth.UêBut he, being full of the Holy Spirit, looked up steadfastly into heaven, and saw the glory of God, and Jesus standing on the right hand of God,Ucand said, "Behold, I see the heavens opened, and the Son of Man standing at the right hand of God!"U`But they cried out with a loud voice, and stopped their ears, and rushed at him with one accord.UzThey threw him out of the city, and stoned him. The witnesses placed their garments at the feet of a young man named Saul.UNThey stoned Stephen as he called out, saying, "Lord Jesus, receive my spirit!"U~He kneeled down, and cried with a loud voice, "Lord, don't hold this sin against them!" When he had said this, he fell asleep.t(NUŸSaul was consenting to his death. A great persecution arose against the assembly which was in Jerusalem in that day. They were all scattered abroad throughout the regions of Judea and Samaria, except for the apostles.U9Devout men buried Stephen, and lamented greatly over him.UgBut Saul ravaged the assembly, entering into every house, and dragged both men and women off to prison.UITherefore those who were scattered abroad went around preaching the word.UKPhilip went down to the city of Samaria, and proclaimed to them the Christ.UÅThe multitudes listened with one accord to the things that were spoken by Philip, when they heard and saw the signs which he did.UñFor unclean spirits came out of many of those who had them. They came out, crying with a loud voice. Many who had been paralyzed and lame were healed.U!There was great joy in that city.U†But there was a certain man, Simon by name, who used to practice sorcery in the city, and amazed the people of Samaria, making himself out to be some great one,Uito whom they all listened, from the least to the greatest, saying, "This man is that great power of God."UTThey listened to him, because for a long time he had amazed them with his sorceries.UïBut when they believed Philip preaching good news concerning the Kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men and women.UÄSimon himself also believed. Being baptized, he continued with Philip. Seeing signs and great miracles occurring, he was amazed.U~Now when the apostles who were at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received the word of God, they sent Peter and John to them,UWwho, when they had come down, prayed for them, that they might receive the Holy Spirit;Ubfor as yet he had fallen on none of them. They had only been baptized in the name of Christ Jesus.UFThen they laid their hands on them, and they received the Holy Spirit.UvNow when Simon saw that the Holy Spirit was given through the laying on of the apostles' hands, he offered them money,U^saying, "Give me also this power, that whoever I lay my hands on may receive the Holy Spirit."UyBut Peter said to him, "May your silver perish with you, because you thought you could obtain the gift of God with money!UTYou have neither part nor lot in this matter, for your heart isn't right before God.UpRepent therefore of this, your wickedness, and ask God if perhaps the thought of your heart may be forgiven you.UQFor I see that you are in the gall of bitterness and in the bondage of iniquity."UfSimon answered, "Pray for me to the Lord, that none of the things which you have spoken happen to me."UûThey therefore, when they had testified and spoken the word of the Lord, returned to Jerusalem, and preached the Good News to many villages of the Samaritans.UñBut an angel of the Lord spoke to Philip, saying, "Arise, and go toward the south to the way that goes down from Jerusalem to Gaza. This is a desert."UƒHe arose and went; and behold, there was a man of Ethiopia, a eunuch of great authority under Candace, queen of the Ethiopians, who was over all her treasure, who had come to Jerusalem to worship.UPHe was returning and sitting in his chariot, and was reading the prophet Isaiah.UHThe Spirit said to Philip, "Go near, and join yourself to this chariot."UpPhilip ran to him, and heard him reading Isaiah the prophet, and said, "Do you understand what you are reading?"UeHe said, "How can I, unless someone explains it to me?" He begged Philip to come up and sit with him.UÆNow the passage of the Scripture which he was reading was this, "He was led as a sheep to the slaughter. As a lamb before his shearer is silent, so he doesn't open his mouth.UxIn his humiliation, his judgment was taken away. Who will declare His generation? For his life is taken from the earth."UeThe eunuch answered Philip, "Who is the prophet talking about? About himself, or about someone else?"URPhilip opened his mouth, and beginning from this Scripture, preached to him Jesus.UáAs they went on the way, they came to some water, and the eunuch said, "Behold, here is water. What is keeping me from being baptized?"U␀UÅHe commanded the chariot to stand still, and they both went down into the water, both Philip and the eunuch, and he baptized him.UòWhen they came up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord caught Philip away, and the eunuch didn't see him any more, for he went on his way rejoicing.UxBut Philip was found at Azotus. Passing through, he preached the Good News to all the cities, until he came to Caesarea.t(NUkBut Saul, still breathing threats and slaughter against the disciples of the Lord, went to the high priest,U•and asked for letters from him to the synagogues of Damascus, that if he found any who were of the Way, whether men or women, he might bring them bound to Jerusalem.UnAs he traveled, it happened that he got close to Damascus, and suddenly a light from the sky shone around him.U]He fell on the earth, and heard a voice saying to him, "Saul, Saul, why do you persecute me?"USHe said, "Who are you, Lord?" The Lord said, "I am Jesus, whom you are persecuting.UMBut rise up, and enter into the city, and you will be told what you must do."UUThe men who traveled with him stood speechless, hearing the sound, but seeing no one.UÇSaul arose from the