e name of a Jew, and rest on the law, and glory in God,U^and know his will, and approve the things that are excellent, being instructed out of the law,Ucand are confident that you yourself are a guide of the blind, a light to those who are in darkness,Uja corrector of the foolish, a teacher of babies, having in the law the form of knowledge and of the truth.UsYou therefore who teach another, don't you teach yourself? You who preach that a man shouldn't steal, do you steal?UmYou who say a man shouldn't commit adultery. Do you commit adultery? You who abhor idols, do you rob temples?USYou who glory in the law, through your disobedience of the law do you dishonor God?U]For "the name of God is blasphemed among the Gentiles because of you," just as it is written.UïFor circumcision indeed profits, if you are a doer of the law, but if you are a transgressor of the law, your circumcision has become uncircumcision.UuIf therefore the uncircumcised keep the ordinances of the law, won't his uncircumcision be accounted as circumcision?UìWon't the uncircumcision which is by nature, if it fulfills the law, judge you, who with the letter and circumcision are a transgressor of the law?UeFor he is not a Jew who is one outwardly, neither is that circumcision which is outward in the flesh;Uòbut he is a Jew who is one inwardly, and circumcision is that of the heart, in the spirit not in the letter; whose praise is not from men, but from God.t(NUMThen what advantage does the Jew have? Or what is the profit of circumcision?UUMuch in every way! Because first of all, they were entrusted with the oracles of God.U^For what if some were without faith? Will their lack of faith nullify the faithfulness of God?U∞May it never be! Yes, let God be found true, but every man a liar. As it is written, "That you might be justified in your words, and might prevail when you come into judgment."UãBut if our unrighteousness commends the righteousness of God, what will we say? Is God unrighteous who inflicts