ction of the dead. It is sown in corruption; it is raised in incorruption.U]It is sown in dishonor; it is raised in glory. It is sown in weakness; it is raised in power.UuIt is sown a natural body; it is raised a spiritual body. There is a natural body and there is also a spiritual body.UnSo also it is written, "The first man, Adam, became a living soul." The last Adam became a life-giving spirit.UeHowever that which is spiritual isn't first, but that which is natural, then that which is spiritual.UTThe first man is of the earth, made of dust. The second man is the Lord from heaven.UÉAs is the one made of dust, such are those who are also made of dust; and as is the heavenly, such are they also that are heavenly.U\As we have borne the image of those made of dust, let's also bear the image of the heavenly.U~Now I say this, brothers, that flesh and blood can't inherit the Kingdom of God; neither does corruption inherit incorruption.UPBehold, I tell you a mystery. We will not all sleep, but we will all be changed,Uúin a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet will sound, and the dead will be raised incorruptible, and we will be changed.UWFor this corruptible must put on incorruption, and this mortal must put on immortality.U¨But when this corruptible will have put on incorruption, and this mortal will have put on immortality, then what is written will happen: "Death is swallowed up in victory."U;"Death, where is your sting? Hades, where is your victory?"U;The sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.UMBut thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.UöTherefore, my beloved brothers, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the Lord's work, because you know that your labor is not in vain in the Lord.t(NUhNow concerning the collection for the saints, as I commanded the assemblies of Galatia, you do likewise.UsOn the first day of the week, let each one of you save, as he may prosper, that no collections be made when I come.UeWhen I arrive, I will send whoever you approve with letters to carry your gracious gift to Jerusalem.U=If it is appropriate for me to go also, they will go with me.U`But I will come to you when I have passed through Macedonia, for I am passing through Macedonia.UjBut with you it may be that I will stay, or even winter, that you may send me on my journey wherever I go.UfFor I do not wish to see you now in passing, but I hope to stay a while with you, if the Lord permits.U+But I will stay at Ephesus until Pentecost,UPfor a great and effective door has opened to me, and there are many adversaries.UkNow if Timothy comes, see that he is with you without fear, for he does the work of the Lord, as I also do.UäTherefore let no one despise him. But set him forward on his journey in peace, that he may come to me; for I expect him with the brothers.U∂Now concerning Apollos, the brother, I strongly urged him to come to you with the brothers; and it was not at all his desire to come now; but he will come when he has an opportunity.U9Watch! Stand firm in the faith! Be courageous! Be strong!U$Let all that you do be done in love.UòNow I beg you, brothers (you know the house of Stephanas, that it is the first fruits of Achaia, and that they have set themselves to serve the saints),UYthat you also be in subjection to such, and to everyone who helps in the work and labors.UwI rejoice at the coming of Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus; for that which was lacking on your part, they supplied.UVFor they refreshed my spirit and yours. Therefore acknowledge those who are like that.UÖThe assemblies of Asia greet you. Aquila and Priscilla greet you much in the Lord, together with the assembly that is in their house.U?All the brothers greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.U/This greeting is by me, Paul, with my own hand.UOIf any man doesn't love the Lord Jesus Christ, let him be accursed. Come, Lord!U/The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with you.U,My