ed us in part, that we are your boasting, even as you also are ours, in the day of our Lord Jesus.U`In this confidence, I was determined to come first to you, that you might have a second benefit;UÅand by you to pass into Macedonia, and again from Macedonia to come to you, and to be sent forward by you on my journey to Judea.UΩWhen I therefore was thus determined, did I show fickleness? Or the things that I purpose, do I purpose according to the flesh, that with me there should be the "Yes, yes" and the "No, no?"UABut as God is faithful, our word toward you was not "Yes and no."UåFor the Son of God, Jesus Christ, who was preached among you by us, by me, Silvanus, and Timothy, was not "Yes and no," but in him is "Yes."UàFor however many are the promises of God, in him is the "Yes." Therefore also through him is the "Amen," to the glory of God through us.UFNow he who establishes us with you in Christ, and anointed us, is God;UMwho also sealed us, and gave us the down payment of the Spirit in our hearts.UTBut I call God for a witness to my soul, that I didn't come to Corinth to spare you.UuNot that we have lordship over your faith, but are fellow workers with you for your joy. For you stand firm in faith.t(NUOBut I determined this for myself, that I would not come to you again in sorrow.USFor if I make you sorry, then who will make me glad but he who is made sorry by me?UøAnd I wrote this very thing to you, so that, when I came, I wouldn't have sorrow from them of whom I ought to rejoice; having confidence in you all, that my joy would be shared by all of you.U∂For out of much affliction and anguish of heart I wrote to you with many tears, not that you should be made sorry, but that you might know the love that I have so abundantly for you.UuBut if any has caused sorrow, he has caused sorrow, not to me, but in part (that I not press too heavily) to you all.ULSufficient to such a one is this punishment which was inflicted by the many;Uïso that on the contrary you should