sses.UâI command you before God, who gives life to all things, and before Christ Jesus, who before Pontius Pilate testified the good confession,Udthat you keep the commandment without spot, blameless, until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ;Umwhich in its own times he will show, who is the blessed and only Ruler, the King of kings, and Lord of lords;Uâwho alone has immortality, dwelling in unapproachable light; whom no man has seen, nor can see: to whom be honor and eternal power. Amen.U«Charge those who are rich in this present world that they not be haughty, nor have their hope set on the uncertainty of riches, but on the living God, who richly provides us with everything to enjoy;Umthat they do good, that they be rich in good works, that they be ready to distribute, willing to communicate;Uulaying up in store for themselves a good foundation against the time to come, that they may lay hold of eternal life.UèTimothy, guard that which is committed to you, turning away from the empty chatter and oppositions of the knowledge which is falsely so called;UOwhich some professing have erred concerning the faith. Grace be with you. Amen.ttq7(U	2 Timothy(NUxPaul, an apostle of Jesus Christ through the will of God, according to the promise of the life which is in Christ Jesus,Ueto Timothy, my beloved child: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.UâI thank God, whom I serve as my forefathers did, with a pure conscience. How unceasing is my memory of you in my petitions, night and dayUJlonging to see you, remembering your tears, that I may be filled with joy;U°having been reminded of the unfeigned faith that is in you; which lived first in your grandmother Lois, and your mother Eunice, and, I am persuaded, in you also.UwFor this cause, I remind you that you should stir up the gift of God which is in you through the laying on of my hands.UNFor God didn't give us a spirit of fear, but of power, love, and self-control.UïTherefore don't be asha