ngs.U\Remember Jesus Christ, risen from the dead, of the seed of David, according to my Good News,U^in which I suffer hardship to the point of chains as a criminal. But God's word isn't chained.UçTherefore I endure all things for the chosen ones' sake, that they also may obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus with eternal glory.UNThis saying is faithful: "For if we died with him, we will also live with him.UPIf we endure, we will also reign with him. If we deny him, he also will deny us.UAIf we are faithless, he remains faithful. He can't deny himself."UöRemind them of these things, charging them in the sight of the Lord, that they don't argue about words, to no profit, to the subverting of those who hear.UÇGive diligence to present yourself approved by God, a workman who doesn't need to be ashamed, properly handling the Word of Truth.UEBut shun empty chatter, for they will proceed further in ungodliness,UMand their word will consume like gangrene, of whom is Hymenaeus and Philetus;Uzmen who have erred concerning the truth, saying that the resurrection is already past, and overthrowing the faith of some.U¨However God's firm foundation stands, having this seal, "The Lord knows those who are his," and, "Let every one who names the name of the Lord depart from unrighteousness."UèNow in a large house there are not only vessels of gold and of silver, but also of wood and of clay. Some are for honor, and some for dishonor.UöIf anyone therefore purges himself from these, he will be a vessel for honor, sanctified, and suitable for the master's use, prepared for every good work.UFlee from youthful lusts; but pursue righteousness, faith, love, and peace with those who call on the Lord out of a pure heart.UPBut refuse foolish and ignorant questionings, knowing that they generate strife.UWThe Lord's servant must not quarrel, but be gentle towards all, able to teach, patient,U}in gentleness correcting those who oppose him: perhaps God may give them repentance leading to 