ho will judge the living and the dead at his appearing and his Kingdom:Utpreach the word; be urgent in season and out of season; reprove, rebuke, and exhort, with all patience and teaching.UùFor the time will come when they will not listen to the sound doctrine, but, having itching ears, will heap up for themselves teachers after their own lusts;UGand will turn away their ears from the truth, and turn aside to fables.UiBut you be sober in all things, suffer hardship, do the work of an evangelist, and fulfill your ministry.UFFor I am already being offered, and the time of my departure has come.UPI have fought the good fight. I have finished the course. I have kept the faith.UÃFrom now on, there is stored up for me the crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the righteous judge, will give to me on that day; and not to me only, but also to all those who have loved his appearing.UBe diligent to come to me soon,Uyfor Demas left me, having loved this present world, and went to Thessalonica; Crescens to Galatia, and Titus to Dalmatia.U\Only Luke is with me. Take Mark, and bring him with you, for he is useful to me for service.UBut I sent Tychicus to Ephesus.UiBring the cloak that I left at Troas with Carpus when you come, and the books, especially the parchments.U`Alexander, the coppersmith, did much evil to me. The Lord will repay him according to his works,U?of whom you also must beware; for he greatly opposed our words.U^At my first defense, no one came to help me, but all left me. May it not be held against them.UΩBut the Lord stood by me, and strengthened me, that through me the message might be fully proclaimed, and that all the Gentiles might hear; and I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.UéAnd the Lord will deliver me from every evil work, and will preserve me for his heavenly Kingdom; to whom be the glory forever and ever. Amen.U6Greet Prisca and Aquila, and the house of Onesiphorus.UBErastus remained at Corinth, but I left Trophimus at Miletus sick.UkBe