er is in the darkness, and walks in the darkness, and doesn't know where he is going, because the darkness has blinded his eyes.UXI write to you, little children, because your sins are forgiven you for his name's sake.U…I write to you, fathers, because you know him who is from the beginning. I write to you, young men, because you have overcome the evil one. I write to you, little children, because you know the Father.U—I have written to you, fathers, because you know him who is from the beginning. I have written to you, young men, because you are strong, and the word of God remains in you, and you have overcome the evil one.UzDon't love the world, neither the things that are in the world. If anyone loves the world, the Father's love isn't in him.UâFor all that is in the world, the lust of the flesh, the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life, isn't the Father's, but is the world's.UUThe world is passing away with its lusts, but he who does God's will remains forever.U´Little children, these are the end times, and as you heard that the Antichrist is coming, even now many antichrists have arisen. By this we know that it is the final hour.U¬They went out from us, but they didn't belong to us; for if they had belonged to us, they would have continued with us. But they left, that they might be revealed that none of them belong to us.UDYou have an anointing from the Holy One, and you all have knowledge.UxI have not written to you because you don't know the truth, but because you know it, and because no lie is of the truth.UyWho is the liar but he who denies that Jesus is the Christ? This is the Antichrist, he who denies the Father and the Son.UgWhoever denies the Son, the same doesn't have the Father. He who confesses the Son has the Father also.U¿Therefore, as for you, let that remain in you which you heard from the beginning. If that which you heard from the beginning remains in you, you also will remain in the Son, and in the Father.U;This is the promise which he promised us, the eternal life.UNThese things I have written to you concerning those who would lead you astray.U¯As for you, the anointing which you received from him remains in you, and you don't need for anyone to teach you. But as his anointing teaches you concerning all things, and is true, and is no lie, and even as it taught you, you will remain in him.U}Now, little children, remain in him, that when he appears, we may have boldness, and not be ashamed before him at his coming.UdIf you know that he is righteous, you know that everyone who practices righteousness is born of him.t(NUßBehold, how great a love the Father has bestowed on us, that we should be called children of God! For this cause the world doesn't know us, because it didn't know him.UØBeloved, now we are children of God, and it is not yet revealed what we will be. But we know that, when he is revealed, we will be like him; for we will see him just as he is.UKEveryone who has this hope set on him purifies himself, even as he is pure.U?Everyone who sins also commits lawlessness. Sin is lawlessness.UJYou know that he was revealed to take away our sins, and in him is no sin.UTWhoever remains in him doesn't sin. Whoever sins hasn't seen him, neither knows him.UmLittle children, let no one lead you astray. He who does righteousness is righteous, even as he is righteous.U¶He who sins is of the devil, for the devil has been sinning from the beginning. To this end the Son of God was revealed, that he might destroy the works of the devil.UxWhoever is born of God doesn't commit sin, because his seed remains in him; and he can't sin, because he is born of God.U§In this the children of God are revealed, and the children of the devil. Whoever doesn't do righteousness is not of God, neither is he who doesn't love his brother.U\For this is the message which you heard from the beginning, that we should love one another;Uåunlike Cain, who was of the evil one, and killed his brother. Why did he kill him? Because his works were evil, and his brother's righteous.U8Don't be surprised, my brothers, if the world hates you.UÉWe know that we have passed out of death into life, because we love the brothers. He who doesn't love his brother remains in death.UiWhoever hates his brother is a murderer, and you know that no murderer has eternal life remaining in him.UpBy this we know love, because he laid down his life for us. And we ought to lay down our lives for the brothers.UòBut whoever has the world's goods, and sees his brother in need, and closes his heart of compassion against him, how does the love of God remain in him?UeMy little children, let's not love in word only, neither with the tongue only, but in deed and truth.UQAnd by this we know that we are of the truth, and persuade our hearts before him,UVbecause if our heart condemns us, God is greater than our heart, and knows all things.UEBeloved, if our hearts don't condemn us, we have boldness toward God;U|and whatever we ask, we receive from him, because we keep his commandments and do the things that are pleasing in his sight.UÅThis is his commandment, that we should believe in the name of his Son, Jesus Christ, and love one another, even as he commanded.UÉHe who keeps his commandments remains in him, and he in him. By this we know that he remains in us, by the Spirit which he gave us.t(NUçBeloved, don't believe every spirit, but test the spirits, whether they are of God, because many false prophets have gone out into the world.UqBy this you know the Spirit of God: every spirit who confesses that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is of God,UÀand every spirit who doesn't confess that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is not of God, and this is the spirit of the antichrist, of whom you have heard that it comes. Now it is in the world already.UyYou are of God, little children, and have overcome them; because greater is he who is in you than he who is in the world.USThey are of the world. Therefore they speak of the world, and the world hears them.UóWe are of God. He who knows God listens to us. He who is not of God doesn't listen to us. By this we know the spirit of truth, and the spirit of error.UkBeloved, let us love one another, for love is of God; and everyone who loves is born of God, and knows God.U6He who doesn't love doesn't know God, for God is love.U|By this God's love was revealed in us, that God has sent his one and only Son into the world that we might live through him.UuIn this is love, not that we loved God, but that he loved us, and sent his Son as the atoning sacrifice for our sins.UHBeloved, if God loved us in this way, we also ought to love one another.UrNo one has seen God at any time. If we love one another, God remains in us, and his love has been perfected in us.UZBy this we know that we remain in him and he in us, because he has given us of his Spirit.UUWe have seen and testify that the Father has sent the Son as the Savior of the world.URWhoever confesses that Jesus is the Son of God, God remains in him, and he in God.UàWe know and have believed the love which God has for us. God is love, and he who remains in love remains in God, and God remains in him.UéIn this love has been made perfect among us, that we may have boldness in the day of judgment, because as he is, even so are we in this world.UÅThere is no fear in love; but perfect love casts out fear, because fear has punishment. He who fears is not made perfect in love.U'We love Him, because he first loved us.U°If a man says, "I love God," and hates his brother, he is a liar; for he who doesn't love his brother whom he has seen, how can he love God whom he has not seen?UVThis commandment we have from him, that he who loves God should also love his brother.t(NU{Whoever believes that Jesus is the Christ is born of God. Whoever loves the father also loves the child who is born of him.U]By this we know that we love the children of God, when we love God and keep his commandments.U^For this is the love of God, that we keep his commandments. His commandments are not grievous.UmFor whatever is born of God overcomes the world. This is the victory that has overcome the world: your faith.UTWho is he who overcomes the world, but he who believes that Jesus is the Son of God?U±This is he who came by water and blood, Jesus Christ; not with the water only, but with the water and the blood. It is the Spirit who testifies, because the Spirit is the truth.U For there are three who testify:UAthe Spirit, the water, and the blood; and the three agree as one.UáIf we receive the witness of men, the witness of God is greater; for this is God's testimony which he has testified concerning his Son.U√He who believes in the Son of God has the testimony in himself. He who doesn't believe God has made him a liar, because he has not believed in the testimony that God has given concerning his Son.UUThe testimony is this, that God gave to us eternal life, and this life is in his Son.UUHe who has the Son has the life. He who doesn't have God's Son doesn't have the life.UøThese things I have written to you who believe in the name of the Son of God, that you may know that you have eternal life, and that you may continue to believe in the name of the Son of God.UpThis is the boldness which we have toward him, that, if we ask anything according to his will, he listens to us.UuAnd if we know that he listens to us, whatever we ask, we know that we have the petitions which we have asked of him.UÎIf anyone sees his brother sinning a sin not leading to death, he shall ask, and God will give him life for those who sin not leading to death. There is a sin leading to death. I don't say that he should make a request concerning this.UDAll unrighteousness is sin, and there is a sin not leading to death.U~We know that whoever is born of God doesn't sin, but he who was born of God keeps himself, and the evil one doesn't touch him.URWe know that we are of God, and the whole world lies in the power of the evil one.U∆We know that