ced greatly, when brothers came and testified about your truth, even as you walk in truth.ULI have no greater joy than this, to hear about my children walking in truth.UdBeloved, you do a faithful work in whatever you accomplish for those who are brothers and strangers.UäThey have testified about your love before the assembly. You will do well to send them forward on their journey in a manner worthy of God,UQbecause for the sake of the Name they went out, taking nothing from the Gentiles.UPWe therefore ought to receive such, that we may be fellow workers for the truth.UfI wrote to the assembly, but Diotrephes, who loves to be first among them, doesn't accept what we say.UÙTherefore, if I come, I will call attention to his deeds which he does, unjustly accusing us with wicked words. Not content with this, neither does he himself receive the brothers, and those who would, he forbids and throws out of the assembly.UÄBeloved, don't imitate that which is evil, but that which is good. He who does good is of God. He who does evil hasn't seen God.U{Demetrius has the testimony of all, and of the truth itself; yes, we also testify, and you know that our testimony is true.UWI had many things to write to you, but I am unwilling to write to you with ink and pen;U~but I hope to see you soon, and we will speak face to face. Peace be to you. The friends greet you. Greet the friends by name.tÜqAUJude(NUàJude, a servant of Jesus Christ, and brother of James, to those who are called, sanctified by God the Father, and kept for Jesus Christ:U.Mercy to you and peace and love be multiplied.UŒBeloved, while I was very eager to write to you about our common salvation, I was constrained to write to you exhorting you to contend earnestly for the faith which was once for all delivered to the saints.UÎFor there are certain men who crept in secretly, even those who were long ago written about for this condemnation: ungodly men, turning the grace of our God into lasciviousness, and denying our only Master, God, and Lord, Jesus Christ.U¶Now I desire to remind you, though you already know this, that the Lord, having saved a people out of the land of Egypt, afterward destroyed those who didn't believe.U§Angels who didn't keep their first domain, but deserted their own dwelling place, he has kept in everlasting bonds under darkness for the judgment of the great day.UÈEven as Sodom and Gomorrah, and the cities around them, having, in the same way as these, given themselves over to sexual immorality and gone after strange flesh, are set forth as an example, suffering the punishment of eternal fire.UrYet in like manner these also in their dreaming defile the flesh, despise authority, and slander celestial beings.UπBut Michael, the archangel, when contending with the devil and arguing about the body of Moses, dared not bring against him an abusive condemnation, but said, "May the Lord rebuke you!"UüBut these speak evil of whatever things they don't know. What they understand naturally, like the creatures without reason, they are destroyed in these things.UÑWoe to them! For they went in the way of Cain, and ran riotously in the error of Balaam for hire, and perished in Korah's rebellion.UÊThese are hidden rocky reefs in your love feasts when they feast with you, shepherds who without fear feed themselves; clouds without water, carried along by winds; autumn leaves without fruit, twice dead, plucked up by the roots;UÇwild waves of the sea, foaming out their own shame; wandering stars, for whom the blackness of darkness has been reserved forever.U~About these also Enoch, the seventh from Adam, prophesied, saying, "Behold, the Lord came with ten thousands of his holy ones,Uœto execute judgment on all, and to convict all the ungodly of all their works of ungodliness which they have done in an ungodly way, and of all the hard things which ungodly sinners have spoken against him."UìThese are murmurers and complainers, walking after their lusts (and their mouth speaks pro